Title: IT Business Analyst
Description:
We are excited to speak to you about this opportunity. If you are interested in joining our growing team, please apply to this link directly.
Who We Are
Emphasys Software is the largest full-service provider to serve the public housing, housing finance, and redevelopment marketplace. Across our five divisions, we provide software that modernizes and streamlines complex processes for housing authorities, agencies, lenders, and governments in almost every state. Through our products and services, we help house roughly half of the families most in need within the United States.
Who we need & what’s in it for you:
Emphasys Housing Finance Agency (HFA) division provides products that support multi-family housing, single family loan portfolio management, and financial solutions.
As a Business Analyst with Emphasys HFA, you will help us transform our data into actionable insights to support growth-minded business decisions. You will also establish a framework and knowledge base to demonstrate how our industry-leading products meet customer needs.
Influence and impact. You want to channel your relationship-building, solution-oriented thinking, and technical knowledge to elevate products that will help millions of Americans access the housing services they need.
Professional development. You want to be mentored and supported as you take on the role of a subject matter expert, customer champion, and technical analyst, leveraging data to create solutions for our organization and our customers.
Security. As we enter economic uncertainty, we know it can be hard to consider a career move, but at Emphasys and Aquila, we want you to know that we are stable with expert leaders at the helm and committed to the people who join us.
What you will focus on:
Building insights. You will:
Collect and transform new and existing data to create a knowledge base that demonstrates how Emphasys software products work and benefit our target audience.
Aggregate, digest and analyze internal business metrics, including financial, quality and productivity measures.
Conduct analysis to create a big-picture view and generate actionable insights.
Share data-supported insights with business leaders, provide feedback to enhance operations and features, and identify the strengths and weaknesses of the finished product.
Be the voice of the customer. You will:
Proactively communicate and collaborate with external and internal customers, acting as translator and champion.
Design and deliver documentation, including functional requirements, Business Requirements Documents, Use Cases, GUI, Screen, and Interface designs.
Stay up to date. You will:
Maintain in-depth knowledge of our solutions and services.
Keep abreast of federal, state, and local regulations related to HUD programs that could impact our products and clients.
What you bring:
Education. You have a Bachelor’s degree in a Computer Science or Technology field and familiarity with both business practices and software engineering.
Knowledge and drive. You enjoy working on big-picture data transformation, framework building, customer needs analysis, and feature development planning. You have experience eliciting and writing technical requirements to guide the work of a software engineering team. You have experience balancing multiple concurrent projects and completing deliverables on time.
Technical expertise. You have:
Proficiency with MS Office.
Comfort working in SQL.
Skills to develop BI dashboards.
An ability to design, deliver, and interpret diagrams, data models and documentation.
Ownership. You work with a sense of urgency and hold yourself accountable for exceeding expectations and meeting deadlines. You continuously seek new information and learning opportunities, staying at the forefront of best practices in the industry.
Interpersonal skills. You have a deep appreciation for diverse opinions and approaches. You have flexible and effective communication skills. You can:
Explain technical concepts to a non-technical audience.
Express patience and empathy with customers.
Build impactful working relationships within and across teams.
Why Join
Emphasys Software has been a part of Aquila, a subsidiary of Constellation Software Inc., since 2008. Responsive to the needs of multiple markets, and acting as a thought partner to ensure success, Aquila invests in category-defining B2B/B2G software companies globally. We are a well-managed, profitable company that operates like a startup with the financial backing of a larger organization.
Emphasys brings together bright, talented people who aspire to excellence and share a commitment to upholding our mission: To be a company of outstanding people delivering vertical market software solutions through long-term partnerships with clients.
Our entrepreneurial culture, lean environment, and people come together to form a dynamic organization where purpose drives our growth. With the autonomy to be creative and curious, we collaborate and iterate to achieve real impact in the communities we support.
Apply Now
We encourage and appreciate candidates with diverse backgrounds and experiences. If you have 70% of the qualifications we seek and want to play an integral role in our success, express your interest here.
Emphasys Software promotes equal employment opportunities for all. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, disability, national origin, veteran status, marital status or any other basis covered by appropriate law. All employment decisions are made based on qualifications, merit, and business needs. We welcome and encourage applications from people with disabilities and accommodations are available on request.

Title: DATAA001291 Data Analyst
Company: Northern California Institute for Research and...
Description:
Northern California Institute for Research and Education (NCIRE) is the leading nonprofit research institute in the United States devoted to advancing Veterans health research. NCIRE is part of one of the world’s most dedicated and successful Veterans care communities, pioneering new treatments and understandings of military medicine and care.
Along with our partners at the San Francisco VA Health Care System and the University of California, San Francisco, we are working to discover and develop effective, safe, and practical treatments for military injuries and diseases affecting Veterans. Through new technologies, novel scientific insights, and international clinical collaborations, we strive to set a new standard of health care research for Veterans and military personnel.
Position Definition:
The Data Analyst will work with a jointly appointed UCSF/SFVAHCS Pulmonary and Critical Care Principal Investigator on data analysis of the PI’s research projects. The incumbent will help the PI with a variety of research projects. The successful candidate will independently consult with the PI; plan and implement study projects and analyses; access, manage, merge, and reconcile large databases; apply and develop mathematical models; perform and interpret statistical analyses, including linear, logistic, Cox proportional hazards regression and competing risk models, mixed effect modeling, and machine learning. The incumbent will work with collaborating research faculty and with research fellows and assist with the publication and presentation of findings.
Current active projects include:
Using “big data” to construct cohorts and answer clinically relevant questions in the pulmonary medicine and public health field.
Using “high dimensional” data from human -omics for molecular and functional phenotyping of immune cells in pulmonary diseases.
Essential Functions:
Identify and implement appropriate statistical and predictive models to large datasets.
Communicate analytical results through a variety of written, visual, and oral formats including technical sections of manuscripts, conference posters and presentations, and grants.
Obtain, query, and manage large databases through appropriate data request workflows and computing environments.
Develop study protocols and documentation procedures, and develop and document quality control systems for data validation.
Provide technical support directly and indirectly by acting as the liaison between the research team and technical support.
Suggest novel modeling techniques to foster creative and relevant research.
Job Requirements:
Master’s degree in Statistics, biostatistics, or a related quantitative field.
Experience with a variety of statistical and predictive modeling techniques including logistic regression, mixed effect models, Cox proportional hazard models, and supervised and unsupervised machine learning algorithms.
Experience using programming languages such as R, Python, or SAS.
Familiarity with querying relational databases using SQL.
Strong interpersonal, organizational, written, and oral skills.

Title: Business Data Analyst
Description:
About Obie

Obie is an insurance technology company, hyper-focused on driving value for the modern real estate investor and the partners they work with every day. Whether an owner, lender, agent, or property manager, Obie’s mission is to build technology and insurance products that drive efficiency and fundamentally change the way insurance is bought and sold.

As the industry leader in embedded and instant insurance products, Obie was recently honored as Business Insurance Best Places to Work and one of Inc Magazine's Fastest Growing Companies for 2022. Obie is one of a small number of companies that are both a Y-Combinator and NAR REACH accelerator alum.

To date, Obie has raised $13.7 million from leading proptech investors including Battery Ventures, Thomvest Ventures, MetaProp, Second Century Ventures, and Funders Club. The company has two offices, one in Chicago, IL and the other in Sarasota, FL, but also offers employees the option to work remotely.

Brief Summary of Role

We are seeking an individual to join the growing data analytics team at Obie. Those successful in this role will have a broad mix of business and analytical skills, with depth in at least one of these areas. Those successful will also have strong interpersonal skills and be comfortable communicating with a wide range of individuals in different disciplines and levels.

Although reporting within the broader Risk team, we work in a matrixed environment. The ability to collaborate and build trust with customers within and outside the Risk department is critical. This role will require the skill to complete intermediate tasks with some guidance from your leader.
What You'll Do:
Create critical data visualizations that incorporate best practices to support business needs and provide insights for both internal teams and external partners
Become an expert within Obie’s data visualization tool and train business users on how to use it
Complete priority reporting within Excel, until it can be built within data visualization tool
Complete ad-hoc reports and analysis that provides meaningful insights into the business; work with business leaders to identify opportunities for improvement
Assist with the creation of business glossaries and data dictionaries, including (1) defining key metrics and dimensions used to evaluate the business and (2) maintenance of data metadata and lineage
What You'll Bring:
2+ years of experience in data analytics or data science, ideally within the Property and Casualty insurance industry
Experience using a data visualization business intelligence tool
Strong experience using Excel
Basic experience using SQL to query data within SQL databases
Technical writing skills
Ability to meet deadlines and manage competing demands
Interview Process

We want you at your best, and won't be giving you any gotcha-style questions - we aren't like that. We want to get to know you, hear about what you're interested in, and learn about what you hope to do in the future.

You should familiarize yourself with these resources before continuing:
a. Our company’s blog to learn more about the space we’re working in and where we write about landlord insurance.
b. Check out our Twitter andLinkedIn to get a glimpse of how people interact with our brand and product.
c. Some posts with and about us around the web (Inc 5000, Estate Innovation, Geek Estate Blog, Business Wire, Innovate State)
d. Podcast appearances: (The Ryan Hanley Show, REM #22)

1. Meet us and learn about Obie
You'll first talk to Kara on a 30 minute call; you won't need to prepare anything in advance. The goal of this conversation is to get to know you and mutually explore if we might be a good fit for each other. You'll learn more about Obie and have a chance to ask any questions about our company, team, culture, and product.

2. Meet the hiring manager
You'll get to have a 45 minute video interview with the hiring manager for this role, Jeff White. This discussion will be more technical in nature to ensure you have the skills needed to be successful in the role.

3. Project exercise
This role requires strong Excel skills, so we’ll present you with a challenge to provide you a chance to flex those muscles. You will be able to review the challenge and prep in advance of the live interview with the hiring manager where you'll work through the exercise. We'll be looking to see your Excel, analysis and critical thinking skills - more on this when you get there!

4. Meet the team
Since you'll be joining a close-knit team, we'll ask you to meet other people in the company so we get to know each other a bit better.

Obie has you covered

Being in the insurance industry, we understand the importance of comprehensive benefits for you and your family. These are just some of the benefits and perks we provide:

Competitive salary
Flexible time off with an encouraged minimum time away to support a healthy work-life balance
12 weeks of Paid Parental Leave
Great health, dental and vision coverage
Life Insurance
Flexible Spending & Health Savings Accounts
Stock Options
401k match
Pet Insurance Reimbursement
Equipment budget - everything you need to do your best work
Professional development support
Summer hours

Our Cultural Values
Entrepreneurs at heart, we are a customer first team sharing one goal and one vision. We seek team members who are:
Humble - No one is above another; we all work together to meet our clients’ needs and we acknowledge our own weaknesses
Hungry - We all are driven internally to be successful and to continually expand our contribution and impact
Smart - We use emotional intelligence when working with one another and with clients

Who We Are
KLDiscovery provides technology-enabled services and software to help law firms, corporations, government agencies and consumers solve complex data challenges. The company, with offices in 25 locations across 16 countries, is a global leader in delivering best-in-class eDiscovery, information governance and data recovery solutions to support the litigation, regulatory compliance, internal investigation and data recovery and management needs of our clients.
Serving clients for over 30 years, KLDiscovery offers data collection and forensic investigation, early case assessment, electronic discovery and data processing, application software and data hosting for web-based document reviews, and managed document review services. In addition, through its global Ontrack Data Recovery business, KLDiscovery delivers world-class data recovery, email extraction and restoration, data destruction and tape management.
KLDiscovery has been recognized as one of the fastest growing companies in North America by both Inc. Magazine (Inc. 5000) and Deloitte (Deloitte’s Technology Fast 500) and CEO Chris Weiler has been honored as a past Ernst & Young Entrepreneur of the Year™. Additionally, KLDiscovery is an Orange-level Relativity Best in Service Partner, a Relativity Premium Hosting Partner and maintains ISO/IEC 27001 Certified data centers.

With a clear aspiration to be a trusted catalyst of transformative effect across VF, we live by these values:

About the Role
The Sr Analyst, Brand Data Visualization and modelling will be a dedicated resource to VF’s Vans brand and work closely with the Vans’ Global Digital Strategy team to interface with business stakeholders and peers to meet the business’ analytical needs while managing and developing the Analytics team. Establish and maintain principles, role definitions, responsibilities, standards, procedures, and accountability for data development practices, reporting and visualization

Required Knowledge, Capabilities and Experience:

Experience with multiple systems in any of the following areas including; AWS (S3, Redshift), Alteryx, Power BI, BI HANA, Tableau, SAP BODS , SQL Server, MySQL, Data Warehouse Appliances, Oracle, Teradata, Looker, SAS, SPSS, ThoughtSpot, Cognos, Datorama, Domo, Denodo, and other related products
Demonstrated understanding of retail, wholesale, CPG, or footwear and apparel industry business processes and how data is used within them, with awareness of industry processes and data sets including Demand, Inventory and Supply Planning, Financial Analysis and Forecasting, Product Data, Point of Sale (POS) Data, Buy Planning, Marketing Campaign Management, Social Media Data – Facebook Business Manager, Google Analytics, Big Query, Google Ads, Consumer Data such as Experian Mosaic

Strong project management skills

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
We are recruiting a data analyst to participate on a multi-disciplinary research team with scientists and clinicians to develop tools to analyze large genomic data sets and other -omic data sets to facilitate the development of CRISPR gene therapy for neurologic disease. The analyst will gather, analyze and interpret a wide variety of research data, including publicly available whole genome data sets, patient genome data sets, RNA data sets and proteomic data sets. Analyst will use data inference, data mining, analytics and appropriate statistical methods. Proficiency with python, Java, SQL, Ruby, JavaScript (and TypeScript), C required. Familiarity with genomic data sets, VCF files, and genomic bioinformatics required. Analyst will build new tools to analyze sequencing, RNA and protein data, trouble shoot code, and develop and maintain an interface for researchers to data mine existing and future data sets. This includes establishing and maintaining a server. All tools built and data analysis will be under the supervision of the PI, Claire Clelland.

Throughout the Department of Neurology at UCSF, our mission is to deliver superb patient care, to apply state-of-the-art translational research methods to discover the causes of and treatments for human nervous system disorders, and to educate each generation of medical students, neurology residents and postdoctoral fellows. By fostering cross-disciplinary interactions among scientists around the world, we accelerate the pace of discovery and champion the University's global health initiatives.

Experience with whole genome sequencing data sets, VCF files

Work directly with the acquisition team to help identify opportunities and trends in campaigns targeting millions of customers.

Help our teams operate smarter by creating self service access to their key performance data via dashboards and alerts.

Title: Business Data Analyst
Description:
Overview:
The Business Data Analyst is responsible to provide data quality assessment, data analysis, pattern and trend identification and data visualization. This position utilizes company systems and databases to extract and analyze data to interpret trends and work with management to make effective business decisions. This position demonstrates a team oriented approach, and strives to achieve superior customer service.
Responsibilities:
ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS
Interpret data and analyze results using statistical techniques.
Work with upper management to prioritize business and information needs and identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets based on those needs.
Locate and define new process improvement opportunities, and productivity measures for the individual Business Units.
Manage and query relational databases and monitor for trends, errors and inconsistencies.
Create data visualizations to enable management team to make informed business decisions.
Analyze data and identify opportunities to support successful reporting enhancements.
Create and present ad hoc data analysis, reports and dashboards to inform members of management on sales metrics.
Develop predictive models that help make triaging, pricing or other business decisions.
Develop Tableau dashboards and visualization on customer engagement, revenue and promotions to measure the impacts of various business actions.
Act as the technical SME for groups across the business in regards to sources data, customer process, data manipulation, and analysis techniques(modeling, predictive analytics and data science)
Conduct exploratory analytics to understand data anomalies and elevate meaningful observations for further analysis.
Maintain integrity and quality of data and assure data conformity meets operational requirements and goals.
Assist in planning, establishing and monitoring criteria for data collection.
Ensure report requirements are translated, formatted and integrated into project design and is understood by key stakeholders.
Research Industry data to accurately and granularly classify spend into industry-specific schema.
Build data intelligence around business rules to deliver reportable and actionable information to business leaders.
Create and automate monthly and quarterly sales reports.
All other duties as assigned by management.

Education and/or Experience
Bachelor degree in business or finance. A minimum of two years’ experience preferably in the healthcare or insurance field.

Must be able to follow instructions and respond to managements’ directions accurately.
Must possess advanced skills in Excel, including Pivot tables, VLOOKUP, INEX/MATCH and data tables.
Must be able to intuitively understand if data looks correct and use a variety of tools and techniques to accomplish data validation and visualization.
Must have advanced skills in SQL, PowerPoint, Tableau, SAS and VBA.
Demonstrate accuracy and thoroughness. Look for ways to improve and promote quality and monitor own work to ensure quality is met.

Must be able to work independently, prioritize work activities and use time efficiently.
Must be able to maintain confidentiality.
Must be able to demonstrate team behavior and promote a team-oriented environment.
Must be able to stay focused and concentrate in close quarters under normal or heavy distractions; must be able to work well under pressure and or stressful conditions.
Adapt to change in work environment with the ability to manage change, delays, or unexpected events.
Ability to follow all company policies and procedures in effect at time of hire and as they may change or be added from time to time.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
REMOTE - Kaimetrix, L.L.C. is seeking a professional Data Analyst to support our Federal Government customer, Defense Travel Management Office (DTMO). This position is remote.
The Data Analyst is responsible for a wide range of tasks, including creating data sets, reports, providing data for Tableau processing and usage, assisting in data integration, data quality and Tableau dashboard development to support performance management.
The following tasks are required:
Develop and maintain R and Python scripts
Produce database development/data extraction using Structured Query Language (SQL) skills to create reporting queries and perform analysis on the database
Maintain and create system pipelines that perform data cleansing, aggregation, integration, and other necessary actions
Identify opportunities to improve, streamline, and automate processes
Create Tableau dashboards and download and utilize Tableau dashboard data
Assist in data integration using standard techniques
Analyze and implement data quality improvements
Use research and analysis to recommend best practices in commercial operational and financial travel data
Provide expert understanding of the principles and methods for evaluating program or organizational performance using financial and nonfinancial measures to include identification of evaluation factors, metrics, and outcomes
Apply project management skills to oversee implementation of new data sources and oversee minor projects (systemic data correction, table modification and data population)
Support the development, implementation, and maintenance of strategic and operational performance metrics to assist the government in measuring the effectiveness and efficiency of the DoD Travel Enterprise including key performance indicators (KPIs), performance reports, and dashboards for managers, executive leadership, and other stakeholders to track program performance and assess the overall health of the DoD Travel Enterprise
Document the organization's current business process flows
Identify and document functional requirements for information systems
Develop project documentation and user training materials according to program specifications
Ensure all products delivered demonstrate expert level technical writing skills, both to document reporting/design requirements and communicate effectively with customers and vendors (e.g., data dictionaries)
Education/Experience:
Bachelor's degree in a related field
5+ years of relevant experience
Strong requirements gathering experience
Prior experience with Tableau, R, and Python
Strong experience with SQL to include writing queries
Active CompTIA Security+ certification
Active or prior government clearance or background check highly desired (i.e., DoD agency background check, Public Trust, Secret/Top Secret Clearance)
Kaimetrix, L.L.C. is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, or national origin.

Title: Business Analyst
Description:
The Business Analyst will conduct analysis to improve the financial and operational performance of the company. This position will involve constant communication with our CEO and finance team during discovery and solutioning. The role requires someone who can bridge strategy to operations and conduct analysis to identify specific performance metrics that will have the most leverage to improve performance.
Primary responsibilities include, but are not limited to:
Analyze current performance of key business trends and initiatives to determine current profitability, identify metrics that have the most direct impact to improve results and recommend tactics to improve performance
While taking direction from CEO and CFO, work collaboratively with members of the Executive Team (functional leaders of Sales, Technology, Customer Success, Product and Content) on analysis, findings and recommendations
In collaboration with Executive Team, develop business cases for key initiatives. Perform checkpoint and “post mortem” analysis to measure initiatives performance against business case expectations
Generate business requirements, gain the approval of executives to ensure they meet the business needs/Convert the business requirements into the technical functional requirements as needed
Develop solutions for a variety of situations and work on projects requiring evaluation and analysis
Collaborate with management and team members and other areas of the organization
Desired Experience & Skills:
1-2 years of experience as a business analyst preferred
Experienced database user including table design, querying, and reporting using SQL and MS Access
Highly proficient with Excel
PowerBI experience a plus
Strong communications skills with ability to clearly present information verbally and in writing
Able to self-manage a diverse and dynamic set of responsibilities, proactively solve problems and / or suggest viable solutions while advancing goals and objectives
Excellent organizational skills; ability to plan and coordinate work, ensure the efficient flow of projects and processes
Ability to define problems, collect data, establish facts, and draw valid conclusions
Ability to collaborate with various stakeholders while ensuring that project scope and timelines are achieved

Title: Data Analyst I
Description:
Data Analyst I
- (3238509)

GENERAL SUMMARY/ OVERVIEW STATEMENT: Summarize the nature and level of work performed. Please note that this section should be written in a paragraph format and provide a broad description of the role and its purpose as well as the reporting structure.

The MGH Cardiovascular Imaging Research Center (CIRC) seeks a dynamic and goal-oriented individual for a Data Analyst I position to work on ongoing and future research studies.

CIRC is a world-leading multidisciplinary academic research center with national and international scientific leadership in clinical trials and machine learning. CIRC faculty have led major NIH- and industry-funded funded clinical trials using cardiac imaging, including the PROMISE (NEJM 2015) and REPRIEVE clinical trials (https://reprievetrial.org).

The Data Analyst I will have direct interaction on a team of approximately 35 people including multidisciplinary faculty, Research Fellows, Clinical Research Coordinators, Project Manager, Grants Administrator, and Grants Coordinator under the guidance of CIRC faculty. The optimal candidate has strong problem-solving skills, and is detail oriented with excellent technical, communication, and team skills. The individual in this position will be responsible for developing and evaluating machine learning models, data management, and statistical analysis of clinical research.

This position is ideal for an individual interested in pursuing graduate school or a career in medicine, public health, or clinical research.

PRINCIPAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES: In order of importance, list essential areas of responsibility, major job duties, special projects and key objectives for this position. These items should be evaluated throughout the year and included in the written annual evaluation. This section should be completed as a bulleted list and explain how the role is performed.

Primary anticipated responsibilities include:
Data and statistical analyses using Python, R, Stata, and similar tools
Development and evaluation of machine learning models involving medical imaging
Data wrangling and data management.
Maintaining Standard Operating Procedures for data management.
Maintaining IT infrastructure and collaborating with MGB IS and external vendors as needed.
Close collaboration with CIRC faculty, research fellows, project managers, and clinical research coordinators
Visualization of data and development of interactive tools
Literature review and preparation of abstracts and manuscripts

SKILLS & COMPETENCIES REQUIRED: This section should be a bulleted list of minimum requirements explaining the skills (what the individual is trained for) and competencies (measurable as defined by the job) necessary to perform the job.

At minimum a Bachelor’s degree, Master’s preferred.
A strong interest in participating in clinical and machine learning research
Proficient with Python, R, and Stata (or similar software).
Willingness to learn and work with machine learning and statistical models.
Strong creative skills for data visualization and analysis.
Ability to perform medical literature searches.
Strong database management and statistical skills
Excellent communication skills, including the ability to interact with physicians and researchers.
Strong work ethic, excellent organization skills, and meticulous attention to detail.

Title: Data Analyst (Remote)
Description:
#WeAreCrowdStrike and our mission is to stop breaches. As a global leader in cybersecurity, our team changed the game. Since our inception, our market leading cloud-native platform has offered unparalleled protection against the most sophisticated cyberattacks. We’re looking for people with limitless passion, a relentless focus on innovation and a fanatical commitment to the customer to join us in shaping the future of cybersecurity. Consistently recognized as a top workplace, CrowdStrike is committed to cultivating an inclusive, remote-first culture that offers people the autonomy and flexibility to balance the needs of work and life while taking their career to the next level. Interested in working for a company that sets the standard and leads with integrity? Join us on a mission that matters - one team, one fight.
About the Role:
CrowdStrike is looking for a Data Analyst to join our Falcon Complete team. As a Data Analyst, you will be responsible for gathering, transforming, and analyzing data, maintaining data quality, creating reports and dashboards, and providing insights to key stakeholders to help them make informed business decisions. You will work closely with leadership to identify business requirements and data needs. You will also partner with other departments to incorporate their data into insights needed for Falcon Complete. Your role will be critical in driving strategic decision-making and supporting operational efficiencies. Your duties will generally vary based on the current business need.
Responsibilities & Expectations:
Work with stakeholders to understand their data needs and provide recommendations for improvements to data sources and reporting processes.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather data requirements and create data visualizations that help drive business decisions.
Partner with CrowdStrike Data Services to ingest data into the CrowdStrike data warehouse to support reporting and analysis needs while maintaining compliance.
Develop and maintain data transforms, datasets, dashboards, reports, and queries with the highest level of data quality.
Perform ad-hoc analysis to identify trends and patterns, and make recommendations based on insights gained from data.
Complete recurring run-the-business tasks including, but not limited to, data snapshots, audits, and project statuses.
Lead Falcon Complete projects pertaining to data migrations between systems and tools.
Implement and maintain a data quality framework to ensure consistent and accurate data.
Effectively communicate insights and data trends to stakeholders.
Provide support, guidance, and training on data warehouse and tooling to Falcon Complete team members as needed.
Create documentation for all aspects of Falcon Complete’s data, including a data dictionary, KPI playbook, dataset details, and other relevant areas of the role.
Desired Skills & Experience:
Bachelor's degree in a relevant field such as Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics, or a related discipline.
3+ years of experience in data analysis and visualization, including experience with SQL, Snowflake, and Tableau.
Must be a U.S. citizen.
This role will require the candidate to periodically undergo and pass additional background and fingerprint check(s) consistent with government customer requirements.
Strong knowledge of and experience with data modeling, ETL processes, and data warehousing concepts.
Proven ability to create effective data visualizations and dashboards that clearly communicate complex information to non-technical stakeholders.
Proven ability to work creatively and analytically in a problem-solving scenario.
Able to comprehend new concepts, ask pertinent questions, execute and document ideas and concepts with little to no day-to-day direction.
Strong communication skills with the ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams, including leadership and other departments.
Strong attention to detail and problem-solving skills.
Advanced experience with Excel is required.
Experience with the following is highly preferred: Jira, Salesforce, LogScale, Splunk

Title: Data Analyst, Underwriting
Description:
Position
The Underwriting Department at WCF has an immediate opening for someone who can demonstrate the WCF values to join their team as an Underwriting Data Analyst. This is a full-time, non-exempt position based in WCF's Sandy, Utah headquarters. Hybrid work combination of office and home available.

Responsibilities
The person in this position gathers and analyzes data used in the underwriting of large accounts for all lines of insurance. This person creates presentations and works with underwriters and leadership in the decision-making process. The Underwriting Data Analyst assists underwriters by gathering and analyzing data used in underwriting large accounts and extracts and evaluates quantitative data from various sources and delivers constructive recommendations based on analyzed results. The person in this position analyzes data using forecasting and analytical tools. The Underwriting Data Analyst also analyzes and reviews loss and safety trends, establishes pricing metrics as defined, and presents conclusions of analyzed data to underwriters. The person in this position organizes and creates presentations using visual methods such as graphs and charts.

Qualifications
The most qualified candidate will have:
Bachelor's degree in statistics, math, finance, actuarial science or related field.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.
Good organizational & critical thinking skills.
Strong working knowledge and capability of Excel and the other Microsoft office products.
Capable of creating charts, graphs, and visuals from data.
Ability to present data in a professional setting to internal and external customers.
Ability to Interact/collaborate/communicate with agencies.
Insurance experience a plus.
Ability to prioritize and meet deadlines.
Is curious and creative in analyzing and presenting findings.

WCF Insurance offers an extensive compensation package. Benefits include Medical, Dental, and Vision insurance, company paid life insurance, 401K with a Generous 6% employer match and additional benefits such as an Employee Assistance Program and time off to volunteer. All employees earn 4 weeks of vacation their first year. Minimum pay is $62,000. Can be more depending on experience and/or education.
An internal candidate should have six months in their current position, acceptable job performance, and must notify their current supervisor that they have applied for the position.

Title: Data Operations Analyst
Description:
Description
About this role
BlackRock is one of the world’s pre-eminent asset management firms and an outstanding provider of global investment management, risk management and advisory services to institutional, intermediary and individual investors around the world! BlackRock offers a range of solutions — from rigorous fundamental and quantitative active management approaches sought at improving outperformance to highly efficient indexing strategies crafted to gain broad exposure to the world’s capital markets. Our clients can access our investment solutions through a variety of product structures, including individual and institutional separate accounts, mutual funds and other pooled investment vehicles, and the industry-leading iShares® ETFs!
Team Overview:
Data Operations and Solutions is entrusted with maintaining all data integral to the investment decision process. The function serves BlackRock the Investment Manager and its BlackRock Solutions (BRS) business, in our proprietary Aladdin® end-to-end investment platform. This team closely partners with key internal teams, such as Portfolio Management, Global Capital Markets, Relationship Management, Portfolio Compliance, Risk Analytics, Regulatory Reporting, and others, to ensure their business data needs are met accurately, timely, and efficiently.
The Data Ops and Solutions philosophy is anchored on BlackRock’s cornerstone principles: Fiduciary focus, Passion for Performance, the unified purpose of One BlackRock, taking Emotional Ownership and Being Committed to a Better Future. Through this lens, we strive to build value for our clients by understanding their needs, the markets, and using technology to create best in class solutions. Our function has presence across 12 offices in 8 countries, servicing more than $25 trillion in AUM on Aladdin for a client base spanning 6 continents and all spectrums of the financial markets.
Within the data organization sits the Quality Control function, which owns security and portfolio level risk analytics quality control along with the governance and design of these QC processes. This team ensures our clients have the highest quality of risk analytics. We do so by focusing on building scale and efficiency by integrating data science to craft and implement a centralized quality control platform for key risk analytics metrics. The team strives to build in-depth subject matter expertise in risk analytics, capital markets as well as BlackRock's proprietary risk models and Aladdin software suite to service that mission.
Responsibilities include:
Daily support of a risk analytics trading process for BlackRock and BlackRock Solutions’ clients.
Learning the intricacies and interconnectivities of Aladdin® end to end investment platform.
Sophisticated research into the risk profile of global investments that involves broad experience in Equities, Fixed Income, Derivatives, and Alternatives, across the vast global investment marketplace.
Daily quality control and validation of intraday risk analytics and providing specialist advice related to reference, index, and pricing data.
Envisioning, designing, and developing enhanced quality control models using machine learning and data science methodologies.
Performing efficiency reviews of internal processes and recommending improvements.
Applying research skills, critical thinking and financial math to analyze macroeconomic and market trends to incorporate into improvement proposals to QC models and methodologies
Close collaboration with market analytics and financial modeling groups to expand understanding of our models.
Interacting with clients to serve as a security-level risk knowledge desk to provide outstanding customer service
Performing testing of in-house programs relevant to owned processes
Ability to operate in an agile environment and employ agile methodology principles, project management and process design
Qualifications:
The applicant must possess and demonstrate an understanding of fixed income, equity, and derivative financial instruments.
You should have the interest and ability to work in a fast-paced and entrepreneurial working environment along with comfort in working closely with teammates on shared projects and objectives.
Have some flexibility regarding their work hours.
Excellent communication skills are required to orchestrate working relationships with internal and external partners.
A bachelor’s degree or equivalent in Accounting, Economics, Finance, Computer Science, or Engineering is required. Non-target degrees will be considered if a solid understanding of global markets can be proven.
A “Student of the Markets” mentality: Intellectually curious with a passion for learning about the global financial markets and the investment management business.
Experience or education related to agile methodologies is a bonus.
Proven grasp and comprehension of technical tools such as SQL, Python and Unix is helpful. PERL is a plus, but not required.
Comfortable working different shifts(10am-7pm M-F, 9am-8pm M-Th)
We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, sex, gender, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request accommodation.
#EarlyCareers

For Seattle only the salary range for this position is $76,000 – $90,000.0. Additionally, employees are eligible for an annual discretionary bonus, and benefits including heath care, leave benefits, and retirement benefits. BlackRock operates a pay-for-performance compensation philosophy and your total compensation may vary based on role, location, and firm, department and individual performance.
Our benefits
To help you stay energized, engaged and inspired, we offer a wide range of benefits including a strong retirement plan, tuition reimbursement, comprehensive healthcare, support for working parents and Flexible Time Off (FTO) so you can relax, recharge and be there for the people you care about.
Our hybrid work model
BlackRock’s current hybrid work model is designed to enable in-person connections and collaboration that is core to our culture, while supporting increased flexibility for all employees. In line with local health guidance and regulations, employees are required to work at least 3 days in the office each week, with the flexibility to work from home up to 2 days a week. Some business groups may require more time in the office due to their roles and responsibilities. The health, safety and well-being of our people will always be our top priorities; we will continue to monitor local conditions and health advisories in making decisions about our work environments.
About BlackRock
At BlackRock, we are all connected by one mission: to help more and more people experience financial well-being. Our clients, and the people they serve, are saving for retirement, paying for their children’s educations, buying homes and starting businesses. Their investments also help to strengthen the global economy: support businesses small and large; finance infrastructure projects that connect and power cities; and facilitate innovations that drive progress.
This mission would not be possible without our smartest investment – the one we make in our employees. It’s why we’re dedicated to creating an environment where our colleagues feel welcomed, valued and supported with networks, benefits and development opportunities to help them thrive.

Title: Data Analyst (Remote)
Description:
NEW DIGITAL BANK MISSION STATEMENT:
Join us on our mission to create a completely new, 100% digital bank that truly serves customers’ best interests. We are a close knit and fun-loving team of seasoned financial services professionals who came together for the challenge of building a bank from scratch – and we are committed to doing it all the right way (from technology infrastructure to modern marketing to customer experience).
We work with the flexibility and speed of start-up. But we also have significant stability and capital from being part of the SMBC Group (Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation). SMBC is the 2nd largest bank in Japan, and the 12th largest bank in the world with operations in over 40 countries. And SMBC is committed to disrupting the US marketplace with ground-breaking products.
It’s the best of both worlds, and we are seeking proven marketing leaders to propel us towards national launch. We have both the ambitious growth plans and the “patient capital” necessary to execute a multi-year plan. Join us on the journey to deliver an exciting concept of evolved banking.

JOB SUMMARY:
Reporting to the SVP, Deposit and Lending Operations Executive, this position will support the insourced operational needs of the Deposits, Lending, Call Center, and Account Application Operations Leaders. The Data Analyst will support a broad range of operations and operational oversight functions for the team.
The Challenge: At launch, our data warehouse will not yet be in place. You will source data from various de-centralized sources to create reporting and visualizations. You will have the experience and imagination necessary to efficiently create and provide this analysis. Your skills with Python, SQL, Power BI, or Google Analytics will help you here. As the Data Warehouse is built, you will be our key source of report building and analysis from this environment. Your skills with analysis and lean thinking will now come into play as you apply DMAIC to identify and improve processes. Eventually, this positions journey will lead towards Machine Learning and Robotics, with tools such as Automation Anywhere or Blue Prism, to automate functions and build efficiency.
Who you are: You likely have a couple of years of experience and are a fan of data and data analysis tools and continuous improvement. You have these skills and certifications as a minimum. You might already be on a Six Sigma or Lean certification path. You know the future is automation, and you either have skills in this field, or plan to have them on your educational journey.

PRINCIPAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
Develop and manage programs/initiatives for data quality, change control, governance.
Identify, manage, and review data quality metrics for internal and external reporting and provide input into communication routines with stakeholders, business partners, and senior leaders.
Design and conduct analysis to identify and remediate change controls, data quality, or integrity issues to identify and remediate process or control gaps.
Analyze, assess, and test data controls and data systems to ensure quality and risk compliance standards are met including developing recommendations for optimal approaches to resolve data quality issues.
Execute internal data quality audits to benchmark the state of data quality.
Provide key support to JB Audit and RCSA activities.
Assists VP, and AVPs with developing and maintaining the Risk Control Self-Assessment.
Work with business and technology partners or subject matter professionals to document or maintain business or data elements or data-related controls.
Consult with internal partners to assess the current state of data quality within the area of assigned responsibility.
Recommend plans for the development and implementation of initiatives that assess the quality of new data sources.
Plan and support implementation of data migration to new tooling including drafting requirements, performing assessments on quality of new data sources, designing, and supporting cross functional user testing.

Title: Data Analyst, E-commerce and DTC
Description:
Who You Are: You have an innate talent for mining e-com data, providing analysis, and making recommendations for what to do with your findings. You have an entrepreneurial spirit, are endlessly curious, are driven by a growth mindset, and have a passion for all things data and e-commerce!
The Task At Hand: The Data Analyst, E-commerce and DTC reports directly to the Senior Director, Digital Marketing and E-commerce and plays a critical role in sales forecasting and providing business insights to accelerate profitable growth within our direct-to-consumer channel. This highly cross-functional position will be the go-to for all things data-related for the growing E-commerce channel.
In This Role, You Will:
Own the analysis and reporting of key data inputs for our DTC business, including sales, retention, churn, order frequency, etc., monitor ROI of marketing spend, and bring forward insights to aid in the development of programs to drive revenue, loyalty retention and CLTV
Provide weekly reporting and insights to support day-to-day business management, including demand planning and forecasting, inventory management, promotions, marketing programs
Deliver monthly e-commerce sales and revenue forecast along with SKU-level demand forecast leveraging historical trends and marketing spend and activity to ensure accuracy
Perform ongoing customer segmentation analysis to understand better the most loyal and at-risk customers to aid in developing programs to address relevant cohorts and to define acquisition targets for prospecting and maximizing RFM
Deep dive into the DTC portfolio to understand product interactions and ongoing trends to inform opportunities for cross-selling incrementality, SKU rationalization, product inventory gaps, and or pricing optimization opportunities
Partner with the digital team to help optimize marketing efficiency and effectiveness, including analyzing A/B testing results across channels to drive customer conversion and retention
Ensure ongoing data integrity and data security; works to continuously optimize tools and processes for efficiency; document business requirements, processes, and data mapping for stakeholders
Publish regular KPI dashboards and reports to executive leadership and the Board of Directors
Must Haves:
One to three years of professional experience as a business or sales analyst or in a role conducting forecasting, sales reporting, marketing mix modeling, data modeling
Experience in a direct-to-consumer e-commerce business, ideally experience with a subscription business within the CPG or the food and beverage retail industry
Degree in Business, Data Science, Information Systems, or Statistics with related work experience, or equivalent years of professional experience preferred
Knowledge of data warehouse fundamentals and development
Advance knowledge of SQL or similar querying language, ELT and ETL tools, Google Analytics, media metrics and reporting tools, marketing attribution models, data visualization tools
Experience modeling disparate data sets and visualizing data with the ability to convey meaningful and accurate insights
Understanding of or strong aptitude to learn digital media metrics, including CPM, CPC, CPA, CAC, CVR, ROAS, CLTV, and all marketing levers to drive a DTC business
Strong project management, organizational skills, and superior attention to detail
Self-starter with the ability to collaborate in a team-oriented environment and the ability to adapt to evolving priorities and business needs
Able to communicate complex ideas clearly and concisely; strong presentation skills
Compensation:
The anticipated salary range for this position is $80,000-$100,000. The actual salary offer will carefully consider a few factors, including your skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Certain positions are eligible for additional forms of compensation such as bonuses, stipends, equity, and role-specific perks.
Additional:

Our Purpose: Drive systemic improvement in childhood nutrition for a healthier, happier, and more equitable world.
Our Business: At Once Upon a Farm, a better story starts here. We're on a greater mission in providing organic, crave-worthy, snacks and meals for children of all ages. Our recipes are crafted with only the best organic ingredients – whole fruits and veggies, cold-pressed (our pouches), or freshly frozen (our meals) to perfection– to support your growing kids at every stage. Each of our organic, non-GMO, non-dairy recipes contains no added sugar and are free from artificial flavors, colors, and preservatives – just simple, real, nutritious snacks your entire family will love.
We support and champion farmers who supply the highest-quality organic ingredients for our foods. We will always fight for and support efforts to drive positive social change and food justice for the benefit of parents, kids, and families. Lastly, we foster an entrepreneurial and collaborative culture that values humility, honesty, passion, positive social impact, and fun.
Our Team: We’re all fully remote, which makes us a highly collaborative, dynamic, and supportive bunch. We share a singular mission to make the world a better place through the highest quality, most delicious, nourishing, and nutritious products made accessible to every home, from our farms to your fridge. And while we’re invested in our product, we’re equally invested in one another's success.
Once Upon A Farm is a purpose-driven brand made up of an inclusive group of individuals with diverse backgrounds, passions, and beliefs. Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Sasaki Strategies, an in-house team of designers, analysts, and software developers, is looking for a new analyst to help us incorporate data into our design and planning work. Sasaki is one of the leading multi-disciplinary design firms in the world, with over 350 employees based primarily in the Boston region and over 700 awards for excellence in our architecture, site, and planning and urban design practices. Our team is a collaborative, cross-disciplinary group. This role will play a critical link between our design and planning services and the increasing use of complex data to inform decisions. The ideal candidate will demonstrate a strong understanding of data cleaning and analysis combined with a passion for finding the “so what” within a dataset that can drive decision-making. Although the preferred location is Boston, MA, we are open to candidates from the Denver & New York offices as well.
We are looking for someone who has an interest in solving problems that benefit people and the environment, is committed to our team’s success, and is excited to learn something new on a regular basis. It is important that you believe in creating equitable and inclusive outcomes both in the workplace and in the work you do.

Supporting data visualization efforts through data processing and analysis
Working with project teams to analyze data, interpret and prepare graphics and other materials to communicate key findings and strategies
Supporting Strategies product development through prototyping and research on emerging datasets and opportunities for new tools, workflows, or another initiative
Requirements
3-5 years’ experience in a data-focused role, preferably related to geospatial or built environment topics
Strong track record of implementing data processing techniques to clean, parse, and store datasets in both flat and database formats
Demonstrated expertise working with Microsoft Excel, Tableau and other tools for data manipulation
Ability to develop consistent, repeatable workflows for processing common data tasks
A collaborative approach to problem-solving and task completion
Experience with using statistical techniques for drawing insights: descriptive statistics, regression analysis, etc.
Additional Desired Skills
Experience with machine learning and other advanced techniques for analyzing and generating data
Experience working with geospatial datasets and programs, including census data and ArcGIS
Basic exposure to code and scripting: python, JavaScript, R and services like AWS
Knowledge of one of our disciplines (planning, architecture, etc.) is ideal but optional

Learn more about Sasaki Strategies at https://www.sasaki.com/practice/expertise/data-design-tools/

Bimbo Bakeries is looking for a confident, self-starter, who is also results-driven and demonstrates professionalism, to serve in this business-critical role of Data Analyst Co-Op. The Co-Op program is a dynamic 5-month, paid, opportunity that affords students a remarkable experience to participate in fast-paced real-world projects. The co-op is designed to further develop strategic project management, analytical problem solving, and managerial leadership skills. Mentors will be designated to guide student collaborations and project work in each area. Students will be exposed to a variety of functional areas such as engineering, operations, and production while earning college credits in various locations nationwide.
This position will supply analytical support to the Sales Technology Team to understand the customer’s performance and provide continuous optimization recommendations at both a brand and customer level. Creating, formatting, and understanding reports of information to allow a more sustainable capability for informing associates across the organization of performance opportunities with market execution. The ideal candidate has experience working with various customer datasets, distilling information, can answer the “so what” of the data, and then can pull it all together with storytelling that answers the “now what.” This position reports to the Senior Director of Sales Technology and is part of the DSDE Center of Excellence.

Key Job Responsibilities:
Access relevant information, interpret results, draw conclusions, and forms recommendations about opportunities to improve sales plan performance
Use data manipulation and analytical tools to define, build and deliver usable, graphical reports that help guide market execution of action based on patterns, behaviors or correlations determined by the inputs

Create data integration requirements and work with IT development and DSDE product teams to craft standard and custom interface specifications for data coming in from customers or third parties and resulting in standard sales action reports or as inputs to other analytical systems
Analyze input customer data to determine identification methods for data quality anomalies and indicators guiding data governance and the use of inputs for reporting, action or other system analysis

Title: Digital Data Analyst
Description:
Company Description

Vericast is a premier marketing solutions company that accelerates profitable revenue growth for the thousands of businesses it serves directly by influencing consumer purchasing and transaction behavior at scale while engaging with over 120 million households daily. We are recognized as leading providers of incentives, advertising, marketing services, transaction solutions, customer data and cross-channel campaign management, and intelligent media delivery that create millions of customer touch points annually for their clients. For more information, visit http://www.vericast.com or follow Vericast on LinkedIn.

Job Description

As a Digital Data Analyst, you will support the execution of the paid social programs for Vericast clients. For this role, you should have a deep understanding of how different social platforms work, an in-depth experience with the implementation and maintenance of tags and pixels and expertise in Google Analytics, attribution models, and consumer paths. The Digital Data Analyst manages complex tasks within the job function. In this position, you will juggle multiple projects and should be driven, detail-oriented, analytical, a strong collaborator and hungry to do great work.

KEY DUTIES/RESPONSIBILITIES
Work in partnership with the Paid Social Manager to develop tagging strategies using Google Tag Manager for measuring attribution and capturing campaign performance in social platforms (Facebook, Instagram and TikTok) 20%
Support social team to evaluate and modify tracking environment when necessary to improve stability, scalability, and troubleshooting, and to fix configuration issues 15%
Implement event tracking, enhanced conversion pixels, tag sequencing, custom tag development, including custom analytics, JavaScript events and triggers in Google Tag Manager, etc. 25%
Craft storytelling for client facing reports in partnership with Insights team 15%
Analyze ad hoc data in support of client campaigns when needed 5%
Work with strategists on campaign optimizations when it relates to changes or updates on tag and pixel 10%
Support wrap-up report development with insights as needed 10%

Qualifications

EDUCATION
Bachelor's Degree in Business, Marketing, or related field (Required)
EXPERIENCE
2-3 years previous experience in data analytics
Extensive experience working with Social Media Data (with online and offline conversions)
Experience with data visualization tools such including Tableau and Google Data Studio; dashboard design and development skills strongly preferred
In-depth experience with the implementation and maintenance of tags and pixels in multiple platforms
Experience running conversion events in Facebook, TikTok, and Google Ad Managers
Social commerce and integrated campaigns experience preferred
Experience correlating Offline Sales to online engagement metrics in reporting
KNOWLEDGE/SKILLS/ABILITIES
Knowledge reading social APIs and troubleshooting
Strong IT skills with a strong understanding of the latest digital technologies such as Google Analytics, attribution models, and consumer paths
Strong analytical skills for interpreting social media and other online data
Familiarity with API connections to Offline Data and ability to help clients troubleshoot issues

Additional Information

Salary: $75,000-$85,000
The ultimate compensation offered for the position will depend upon several factors such as skill level, cost of living, experience, and responsibilities.

Title: Senior Data Analyst
Description:
Perchwell is growing our team to build the workflow data platform for all residential real estate, a $4T industry (roughly 17% of US GDP) impacting the lives of every single American. As a complete market intelligence, search, and collaboration solution, we partner with forward-thinking MLS (multiple listing service) organizations and brokerages to drive the industry forward.
As a team, we have diverse backgrounds, interests and lifestyles, but we are united by our values. We do exceptional work, pay attention to the details, build great products, and have a positive impact on the industry we serve.
What we're looking for
Perchwell is rapidly expanding across the US to new MLS clients with both unique data sources that must be integrated into our data layer and sophisticated analytics requirements. Robust data management and analytics capabilities are therefore key to our future success. We are looking for a senior data analyst to propel our data integration strategies forward, establish and maintain data quality KPIs at scale, and lead a team of junior analysts to meet our customers' needs.
What you'll do
Work cross functionally to complete MLS implementations into our data layer
Collaborate with Perchwell's product and engineering teams to:
Assist in delivering data pipelines across multiple data sources as we continue to launch into new markets
Design and build the tools you'll use to manage new data KPIs
Cultivate real estate data expertise within your team and across the organization
Develop and maintain data quality KPIs with your team to guarantee gold-standard real estate datasets for our customers
Discover, qualify, evaluate, and recommend new data sources to enrich existing datasets
Participate in and help direct the growth of the Data & Analytics team
Required for the role
4+ years of experience in data analytics, including at least 2 years of experience as a senior analyst (preferably leading junior analysts on projects)
Ability to communicate insights to both technical and non-technical audiences
Strong SQL & Python skills
Previous experience in an AWS environment utilizing the breadth of tools available
Must be available to work in Perchwell's NYC office
Bonus points for the following
Knowledge of or exposure to real estate-specific datasets
Previous experience leading a team of junior analysts through project completion
Salary Range:

$80K - $175K per year

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Description:
Data Analyst
This is a high impact and exciting position that will assist in the development and support for Valiant BI, an internal & external platform used by Valiant Residential & their clients. This individual will be responsible for shaping the future of this platform in close collaboration with the senior leadership team. This individual will extensively utilize their Power BI & Python skills to further develop the Valiant BI platform into a scalable and performant cross-BU analytics platform.
More specifically, this role will be accountable for oversight and delivery of data visualization, aimed toward delivering insights for fast and accurate, fact-based decision making. This requires identifying and understanding key issues, strong analytical thinking, the ability to conduct quantitative analysis and develop conclusions based on analysis/research.
Key Responsibilities
Implement robust, reliable and custom reporting and visualizations using Power BI
Develop and maintain self-service reporting solutions and/or automated solutions
Use SQL as main tool for data preparation: extracting, cleansing, aggregation, and summarizing data to create meaningful visualizations
Participate in the design and implementation of logical and physical data models
Review proposed production changes to ensure highest quality data standards and lowest production impact
Navigate, understand, and leverage existing complex data structures for reporting
Proactively make recommendations and identify opportunities to solve business problems through models, charts, graphs, and dashboards
Maintain, update, and distribute client-facing and internal dashboards that track multifamily analytics and Key Performance Indicators
Support production BI solutions by monitoring and tuning SQL queries and data loads
Addressing user questions concerning data integrity
Monitoring performance and communicating functional and technical issues proactively
Interact with senior management, department leaders and other employees to develop and reach agreement on reporting requirements and priorities
Coordinate system development with IT to enhance automation and visibility
Requirements:
Requirements
Bachelor’s Degree in any quantitative field (Business, Math, Finance, Statistics, Engineering).
2+ year work experience designing, developing, publishing and maintaining business intelligence solutions using Microsoft Power BI
Critical Skills
Extensive knowledge of Data Analysis Expressions (DAX), Power Query formula language (M), and SQL
Understanding of source systems, ETL tools, SQL processes to build & debug the sources of visualization data.
Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information quickly
Predictive modeling techniques and statistics using Python, Machine Learning, AI, NLP experience is a plus
Power Automate experience is a plus
Additional Knowledge and Skills
Proven ability to handle multiple projects while meeting deadlines and documenting progress towards those deadlines
High initiative, drive, and energy, self-confidence, and results driven.
Ability to quickly grasp business challenges and drive positive change.
Able to work effectively in a team environment with little or no supervision
Expert in requirements gathering skills, and solving business issues through data-related tools
Real estate experience / multifamily industry knowledge is a plus

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Harvest Overview: Based in Englewood, at the foothills of Colorado's Rocky Mountains, Harvest Strategy Group is the nation's leading end-to-end consumer debt collection management services provider. We hire the best and brightest to provide our clients with customized, national litigation and collection programs to maximize revenue on consumer receivables with enterprise-level audit, Compliance, and oversight. Harvest is small enough (approx. 37 employees) for employees to make an impact, but large enough to offer a competitive compensation package and the opportunity to work with some of the nation's largest financial institutions.
Remote Work Expectations: This position is a Remote Eligible position, which means it can be performed remotely from any location in the continental US, but preference is given to those who live near our headquarters in Englewood, CO. Harvest currently operates in a flexible, hybrid workplace model where employees may choose to work from home or from the office, with the occasional required in-office days to facilitate connection and collaboration. For example, upon hiring, in-office training will be arranged so you can meet and work with those in your department. Most of your work may be performed at home after initial training with occasional in-office meetings once or twice a month for those who live locally. Those who live out of state will be in-office less frequently.
Position Overview: This position will be responsible for the design, upkeep, and direction of the Harvest reporting initiative. In this role, you will design and develop Tableau, Power BI, or similar reporting software reports providing better communication and insight for internal and external audiences. These reports will also provide insights to improve decision-making for clients and the company as a whole. Interfacing with multiple resources such as 3rd party vendors, internal business units, and management is required to understand and deliver the most effective results.
Qualifications
3 years of Microsoft Power BI/stack experience or similar technology.
3 years of experience utilizing M and DAX to conduct data transformations or similar.
3 years of experience with Stitch ETL or equivalent ETL technology.
3 years of experience with BigQuery or similar data warehousing technology.
3 years of experience with dbt - data modeling or similar data modeling skills.
3 years of experience building Tableau, Power BI, or similar reporting software reports and dashboards with a strong design aesthetic.
BS or MS in computer science or information system or equivalent work experience.
Technical Microsoft Power Certifications.
Experience in financial services or accounts receivable management industry.
Experience in the financial services sector.
Position Responsibilities
Oversee reporting processes and enhancements to Harvest’s suite of reports.
Work closely with vendors and internal partners in the design, development, and produce daily, weekly, monthly, and annual reports.
Lead coordination with various business stakeholders to develop, implement, and convert relevant reporting projects.
Understand business requirements to set functional specifications for reporting applications.
Translate big-picture ideas into specific technical requirements for report development and consumable Tableau, Power BI, or similar reporting software reports and dashboards.
Manage the reporting system lifecycle, including the elimination of unnecessary reports.
Convert business requirements into technical specifications and determine timeless for each report implementation.
Maintain system documentation, develop job aids, and provide end-user training and troubleshooting support.
Design, develop, and deploy Tableau, Power BI, or similar reporting software scripts and perform efficient detailed analysis.
Assist with planned reporting migration activities, particularly as it relates to reporting conversion, mapping, revision, and redeployment.
Complete revision, enhancement, and/or expansion of existing report programs to increase operating efficiency or adapt to new requirements.
Personality Profile & Skill Set
Organized: Must be a detail-oriented, well-organized individual who is disciplined and able to work with others and should have reminders or tasks set to ensure that all responsibilities are met on time.
Self-directed: Able to prioritize responsibilities and manage time effectively. Must be able to organize workloads and work areas to maintain a high level of productivity.
Communicative: Ability to articulate thoughts both orally and in writing. Understanding of principles surrounding the responsibilities above. Ability to communicate in a positive manner, even in uncomfortable conversations. Ability to listen and understand the concerns of others. (Very important that communication issues are shared with others involved and that any information needed is acquired.)
Team player: Have a genuine interest in the success of the department and organization. Maintain good working relationships. Be flexible, tolerant, and understanding.
Solution-oriented: Must use analytical and problem-solving skills daily. Be creative in overcoming problems. (Get input from others involved.)
Technology: Independent ability to effectively work within Microsoft Office products and comfortable discussing needs with the IT department.
Background: Due to the clients that we service we require a 10-year employer/ personal background check.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Gordian (www.gordian.com) is the leader in facility and construction cost data, software and services for all phases of the building lifecycle. A pioneer of Job Order Contracting, Gordian’s solutions also include proprietary RSMeans data and Facility Intelligence Solutions. From planning to design, procurement, construction and operations, Gordian’s solutions help clients maximize efficiency, optimize cost savings and increase building quality.

Gordian’s Engineering team sits at the front line of critical research initiatives supporting Gordian’s estimating, procurement, and planning products. In this role, Data Analysts are responsible for report generation, ad-hoc analysis, and operational insights related to core data development. Additionally, Data Analysts apply their expertise to Gordian’s Tailored Solutions products, enhancing ETL processes and guaranteeing the highest level of quality control at all stages of delivery. The Data Analyst will also support the expansion of Gordian’s digital data collection, including web extraction and expansion of ML-driven validation techniques.

The Data Analyst role sits at the intersection of research, specialized consulting, and data product management. In this role, Gordian is looking for someone willing to enhance their skills, foster new and existing industry relationships, and develop deep insight into construction cost data and trends.

Responsibilities:
Responsible for coordinating analytical support of material and equipment research efforts across Gordian’s core data teams.
Take an active, product ownership role in validation and real-time quality control measures for both core data teams and Tailored Solutions products.
Become an expert in the mechanics of construction cost data, and in how it is used by customers to improve estimating and procurement workflows
Support for special projects as needed

Experience Required:
Team oriented and highly collaborative, able to communicate ideas to a diverse audience of internal and external stakeholders
Strong working proficiency with SQL and Microsoft SQL Server. Experience with statistical programming languages R, Python, or SAS preferred but not required
Professional experience with statistical analysis and implementing data quality control process
Experience conducting primary and secondary research is preferred but not required
Experience with construction cost data is preferred but not required
