Title: Senior Finance Master Data Analyst
Description:
Become a Part of the NIKE, Inc. Team
NIKE, Inc. does more than outfit the world’s best athletes. It is a place to explore potential, obliterate boundaries and push out the edges of what can be. The company looks for people who can grow, think, dream and create. Its culture thrives by embracing diversity and rewarding imagination. The brand seeks achievers, leaders and visionaries. At NIKE, Inc. it’s about each person bringing skills and passion to a challenging and constantly evolving game.
With an aggressive long-term growth strategy, NIKE is counting on the Finance function to thrive in its mission to drive and deliver value to every NIKE shareholder. Our consumers are demanding more, increasing the complexity of our business models and need to move faster with greater precision. Nike’s Finance function is on a journey to transform and is strategically investing in tools that allow us to evolve with the Consumer Direct Offense. The Finance Business Intelligence team’s mission is to re-invent reporting and analytics capabilities globally, and we’re seeking world-class talent with a passion for data and analytics, a disciplined focus on business value, and ability to influence change.
WHO ARE WE LOOKING FOR?
We are looking for a Senior Finance Master Data Analyst who is passionate about data management, data transformation, and process excellence. The ideal candidate is skilled in information systems, data structures, and problem solving. This candidate should be comfortable working with a diverse group of partners and communicating and implementing work you're doing with leadership. You will lead transformation efforts in Nike’s Finance Master Data Management strategy and ensure data integrity across Nike’s system landscape.
WHAT YOU WILL WORK ON?
You will support and execute finance master data related tasks while leading efforts on system implementations for process excellence and execution with a focus on data management and data quality. You will work closely with partners to ensure proactive communication of key dates and deliverables, as well as examine existing data structures and future data structures to find opportunities to help partners understand impeding changes. Additionally, you will ensure changes from the business are communicated, tested and implemented with direct partnership with the tech teams and broader Finance Business Intelligence Team. You will have experienced level knowledge on finance master data, key attribution and the impacts on downstream reporting, processes, and application all while assessing, evaluating and recommending improvements or changes to improve existing processes. You will also partner closely with the Finance Data Governance team to provide input on policies and sustain the policies through operation procedures.
WHO WILL YOU WORK WITH?
You will engage with Global and Geo Finance Planning and Controlling teams, Nike Tech teams, Finance Project teams, and the Finance Business Intelligence Team.
WHAT YOU BRING?
Bachelor’s degree (B.S.) in quantitative field such as Statistics, Mathematics, Economics, Business, or Finance
MBA and/or CPA preferred but not required
5+ years of relevant experience– preferably including experience with a national public accounting firm or with a Fortune 500/multinational consumer products company
Experience using, designing, and/or helping to implement MDM tools like Informatica or MDG in sophisticated IT landscapes
Experience using ERP systems like Oracle, SAP, Infor, etc.
Excellent oral, written, and interpersonal communication skills; ability to effectively communicate status, issues, and risks with the team
A consistent track record of delivering results (quality, time, budget) on globally and regionally based projects preferred

Title: Data Quality Analyst (Hybrid- Home & Office)
Location: Hybrid remote in Florham Park, NJ 07932
Description:
Job Purpose:
The Data Quality Analyst will be responsible for all aspects of auditing, analyzing, reconciling, processing and troubleshooting the sales and administrative fee reporting supplied by contracted Business Partners. The Data Quality Analyst will also manage all reporting submissions, including dispensing data, per the terms of the MHA member and Business Partner agreements. An essential part of this position is to resolve discrepancies and perform in-depth audits, analyzing gaps and scouting missing revenue opportunities. The Data Quality Analyst will manage the accurate and timely processing, validation and payment of administrative fees and rebates to ensure accurate reporting is accessible to multiple divisions across MHA. To do so, the Data Quality Analyst will maintain the repository of administrative fee and rebate parameters and schedules while verifying contract terms and working with Business Partners/Vendors and internal departments (Contracts, Membership and Finance).

Essential Duties & Responsibilities:
50%
Validate administrative fee and rebate payments by comparing the Forecast and estimates to Business Partner payments.
Identify and track data and reporting errors or inconsistencies via Audit Process and effectively narrate issues until resolution is found.
Generate missing data and payment reports, follow-up with MHA’s Business Partners for pertinent data files and corresponding payments to ensure timely appending prior to initiating rebate process and audit analysis.
30%
Generate member-level baseline rebate estimates for validation, issuance and distribution by MHA internal Sales and Finance teams.
Ensure that all data, calculations and payments comply with the terms and conditions of the Business Partner, member agreements and corresponding schedules.

15%
Collect sales and purchasing reports from MHA’s Business Partners to calculate and audit administrative fees and rebates that MHA and/or MHA members receive from contracting products
Update applications and/or backend jobs to reflect changes in administrative fee or rebate terms and conditions to ensure that administrative fee reports are properly appended and rebates are accurately calculated and distributed.
5%
Ensure timely and accurate processing and tracking of all assigned Business Partner contractual requirements as well as periodic and ad hoc reports or projects.
Work with Sales and Trade to ensure clarity of rebate terms and conditions prior to execution of rebates.

Minimum Qualifications & Competencies:
Bachelor Degree/Associate’s Degree OR equivalent work experience required.
2+ years accounting data analysis experience where attention to detail and high degree of accuracy preferred.
Ability to efficiently enter data into corporate applications completely and accurately.
Strong proficiency in MS Office applications including Excel (Pivot Tables, V-lookup), Word, and Outlook.
Proficiency in Cognos software application preferred.
Excellent verbal and written communications skills, well organized and the ability to self-manage and work with minimal guidance.
Must have good attitude, interpersonal skills and ability to communicate effectively with Vendors and other external parties.
Ability to comprehensively review and interpret data in order to apply corporate procedures for processing data.
Strong problem-solving skills with ability to identify and resolve data issues in a timely manner.
Excellent organization and time management skills with ability to prioritize work and function independently.
Professional demeanor in performing job responsibilities and when interacting with others.
Attendance and punctuality with commitment to arrive to work on time and ensure work responsibilities are covered when absent.
What MHA Offers:
Competitive salary, including an impressive total rewards and benefits package!
Flexible Paid Time Off, including a hybrid work model, summer hours and at MHA your birthday is a holiday!
Excellent health, dental & vision insurance, with options to fit you & your family’s needs
Your health is important! Our wellness strategy focuses on mental and physical well-being
Casual office dress code – a friendly and welcoming environment
Training & tuition reimbursement program, because continuing to learn matters and we support your development
A dynamic, ambitious, fun work environment
MHA is a growing and evolving service and technology company, and what really makes us unique is our people. Because at our core, we’re a People Powered organization – and our people come first and our culture matters. We’ll help you find a fulfilling career path and encourage you to have a life. Let us be the best place you’ll ever work!

Apply Now!

Description:

Under general direction of the Director of Data Science, the Enrollment Data Analyst will support the Division of Enrollment Management (DEM) as part of a two-person team working within Institutional Research and Effectiveness. Title: Energy Analyst (Data Analysis)
Description:
Position Information
Posting Title
Energy Analyst (Data Analysis)

AE503106

Full-Time

Minimum Qualifications
Education and/or Equivalent Experience:
Graduation with a Bachelor’s degree from an accredited college or university in a field related to Accounting, Business, Finance, Mathematics, Engineering, or Economics, plus three (3) years of experience in utility, regulatory accounting, or rate and regulatory processes.
Graduation with a Master’s degree from an accredited college or university in Accounting or Business Administration may substitute for one (1) year of experience.

Licenses and Certifications Required:
None.

Notes to Applicants
This posting is for an electric-industry Data Analyst who can acquire, analyze and encode data as visual objects contained in graphics for the purpose of communicating insights to decision-makers with clarity, precision and efficiency. Often working under time pressure, the Data Analyst will provide support for executive decisions—“telling the story” in the data. Most analyses will be quantitative and will support Austin Energy’s ratemaking efforts and policy objectives, which include revenue stability for the utility, fairness for ratepayers, and economic efficiency in the provision and use of electric services.

Two major areas of focus will be load data showing the use of the power system by Austin Energy’s customers and customer demographics. As a minority share of total work time, the position may also involve some periodic data reporting, and responding to requests for information from the public and governing bodies such as the Austin City Council.

The successful performer will possess
Solid critical thinking skills,
The ability to package information in a way that engages the audience and influences outcomes,
The ability to formulate hypotheses, seek primary or root causes,
Skill to process, clean, transform data, analyze it, and cite data to reach conclusions; and,
Advanced written and verbal communication skills.

Commensurate

Hours
Monday – Friday (8:00 AM – 5:00 PM)

Job Close Date
04/27/2023

Type of Posting
External

Department
Austin Energy

Regular/Temporary
Regular

Grant Funded or Pooled Position
Not Applicable

Category
Professional

Location
4815 Mueller Blvd, Austin Texas 78723

Preferred Qualifications
Preferred Experience:
Superior skills in quantitative analysis.
Experience directly querying back-end data systems using database querying language.
Experience processing large data sets and mining them.
Experience using data visualization software to “tell the story.”

Duties, Functions and Responsibilities
Essential duties and functions, pursuant to the Americans with Disabilities Act, may include the following. Other related duties may be assigned.

Plans, develops, and presents rate filings for regulated and unregulated energy services.
Models the impact of current or proposed rate strategies on the electric utility’s financial viability including its revenues, cost structure, net margin, liquidity, and debt/equity position.
Conducts financial and economic analysis. Analyzes and monitors sales and revenue data on a monthly basis for each jurisdiction and customer class.
Develops models for revenue requirement and cost of service studies, recovery mechanisms, and rate design.
Develops forecasts including sales, billing determinants, and revenues using statistical and end-use modeling techniques.
Prepares and provides information on market trends, fundamental economic factors, and regulatory filings.
Develops regulatory policies, objectives, and strategies on pricing and cost of service subject matter.
Oversees and develops testimony, exhibits, and tariff changes filed with City Council and State regulatory commissions; provides analytical support; and negotiates and influences outcomes. Presents written and oral testimony as an expert witness in rate proceedings.
Represents the department in supporting initiatives and filings with regulators, key community and customer groups, and other departments. Responds to requests for information (RFIs), appeals, and public cases before the State regulatory authority and City Council.
Provides modeling and other analytical support to develop resource management strategies.
Prepares reports, testimony, and business presentations on the load forecast, highlighting the various drivers such as economic factors, weather, and energy efficiency programs.
Coordinates with metering operations on deployment of sampled customers and collection of interval data in support of load research.
Responsibilities- Supervision and/or Leadership Exercised:
May provide leadership, work assignments, evaluation, training, and guidance to others.

Knowledge, Skills and Abilities
Must possess required knowledge, skills, abilities, and experience and be able to explain and demonstrate, with or without reasonable accommodations, that the essential functions of the job can be performed.
Knowledge of regulatory processes at the State, Federal, and Local level.
Knowledge of transmission revenue requirements, rate design, and rate filing requirements.
Knowledge of potential financial, capital budgeting, and operational impacts of transition to retail access for electric services.
Knowledge of municipal utility finance and accounting.
Knowledge of competitive business practices and analysis.
Knowledge of economic analysis and modeling principles, concepts, and techniques.
Knowledge of power system modeling, statistical modeling concepts, and techniques.
Knowledge of utility economics, as well as utility commission rules and regulations.
Skill in analyzing and monitoring sales and revenue data.
Skill in effective oral and/or written communication.
Skill in resolving problems or situations requiring the exercise of good judgement.
Skill in researching, generating, and analyzing financial and statistical reports.
Skill in using computers and related software applications.
Skill in performing quantitative analysis.
Ability to understand and implement performance based measurements.
Ability to work independently.
Ability to testify in regulatory proceedings.
Ability to work with all organizational levels to influence actions and negotiate outcomes.

Title: Report Writer/Business Analyst - Working from Office

OSU Physicians, Inc.
The Report Writer/Business Analyst will support our clinics by providing the necessary reports that assist the clinics and administrative areas, in operating efficiently. The nature of this position requires you to be in the office to successfully perform the duties.
What will you do?
Under the direction of management, and in collaboration with The Ohio State University Wexner Medical Center (OSUWMC), creates and generates custom/standard reports for organizational initiatives and business operations including but not limited to quality program initiatives to meet regulatory requirements and insurance provider (payor) value-based contracts. Responsibilities include querying Epic/OSUWMC databases, data analysis, data discovery modeling, creating/updating SQL queries, integration of various external data sources, and generation of presentation materials and/or data visualization tools.

Duties and Responsibilities include, but not limited to:
Develops clear and well-structured analytical plans and utilizes data sets to analyze billing, patient populations, business outcomes, and business operations of a significant and sensitive nature. Partners with business leaders to understand analyses and the impact of cause-and-effect relationships.
Maintains an in-depth knowledge of client/department business strategies, processes, and services to aid in data interpretation.
Creates and maintains custom reports on key business areas and indicators to identify and track trending, process improvement efforts and other business outcomes.
Demonstrates analytical critical thinking skills for process development or problem resolution.
Utilizes innovative thinking and tools for optimization of processes, reports and tasks.
Develops written procedures and user documentation for data analysis and reporting
Produces information for administrative, billing and clinical presentations and decision support.
What is OSUP all about?
Our over 60 physician practices in Central Ohio embody the spirit of teamwork with passionate care for our patients and each other. Our teams are diverse in employees, thoughts, and ideas bringing the full spectrum of a collaborative culture to the big picture – TEAMWORK!
OSU Physicians focuses on entire patient experience, from the minute they call in for an appointment, to being welcomed in the office, and then receiving quality, compassionate, thorough care from our physicians and the entire OSU Physicians, Inc., team.
Sound like something you are seeking in your next career adventure? We invite you to keep reading.
What are we looking for in our next new hire?

Bachelor of Science in information systems or related field, or an equivalent amount of work experience.
Knowledge of healthcare database management, data collection, and statistical analysis preferred.
An ideal candidate should have experience in computer applications including proficiency in querying relational databases (SQL is a must), data transformation (e.g. Alteryx) and data visualization (e.g. Qlik, PowerBI, Tableau).
Candidate to demonstrate ability to interpret data specifications to create/generate the files/reports necessary to meet program/contract requirements and create actionable recommendations based off of that data.
Strong communication skills to respond and work with customers, regulatory agencies or members of the business community, along with effectively interacting with different personality types. Demonstrates self-management, personal initiative, willingness to learn new technologies, and ability to work independently while being a team player.
Epic certification in Resolute PB, Epiccare Ambulatory, Healthy Planet and/or Clarity, or a related module is ideal!
What do we offer?
Benefits! It's all about choices. We know that having options and robust benefit plans are important to you. That's why here at OSU Physicians, we offer our employees a flexible, competitive benefit package. Full-time benefits start for individuals working a minimum of 30 hours per week, as well as some benefits available to employees working as little as 20 hours a week. Diverse and Affordable Healthcare Choices: Coverage begins on your First Day of Employment; includes Medical, Dental, Vision and Prescription Drug Programs.

Tuition Reimbursement Program

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About Cirkul, Inc.
Cirkul is a venture backed, direct-to-consumer startup company that develops transformational hydration products that reimagine how flavored beverages are created, personalized, and enjoyed at home and on-the-go. You may have read about us going viral on TikTok (https://www.bizjournals.com/tampabay/inno/stories/news/2021/06/15/tampa-startup-hires-100-after-going-viral-on-tikto.html) or partnering with some great investors here (https://www.bevnet.com/news/2021/cirkul-closes-30m-series-b-led-by-af-ventures/).
Overview
Cirkul is looking for a Data Analyst to join our growing data team. You’ll be tackling challenges across Growth/Marketing, Finance, Retail, Manufacturing, Supply Chain, and Customer Support teams to quickly deliver insights, review and develop metrics, and develop business processes to scale analytics to support a hypergrowth business.
The ideal candidate must be able to roll up his/her sleeves to work independently and contribute to the output and results. He/she must have the ability to prioritize issues, deal with ambiguity and manage conflicting deadlines. The candidate should also be creative, data-driven, and aggressive in delivering results. This position will report directly to the VP Data & Analytics.
Responsibilities
Collect, analyze, and explain data to key stakeholders and executive leadership
Design and develop KPIs tracking business performance across departments
Monitor KPIs to identify potential opportunities to improve company performance
Be a data evangelist: collaborate with both technical and non-technical teammates to supplement decisions with quantitative evidence
Always be auditing: build and maintain processes to track data and troubleshoot errors
Build and automate tools to surface key data to stakeholders across a broad range of data literacy levels
Provide ad hoc analysis and forecasting as needed across a diverse set of teams
Evaluate reporting needs and work with key stakeholders to prioritize overall strategy of the data team in answering company goals
Qualifications
Data-driven, detail-oriented individual with excellent analysis and problem-solving abilities
Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field such as Accounting, Economics, Engineering, Finance, Math, or Statistics or equivalent coursework and work experience
4+ years of relevant industry experience – you have delivered insights in a technical environment and are comfortable doing so again from Day 1
2+ years of DTC, Ecommerce, and/or Retail experience
Fluency in data analysis and data-driven problem solving; a track record of using data to communicate results to key stakeholders
Excellent verbal and written communication skills: the ability to present complex data in a digestible format to stakeholders of all data literacy levels
Fluency with SQL and experience with building models in Excel
Comfortable creating dashboards in a BI framework such as PowerBI, Tableau, Looker, or comparable tools
Ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously: superb time management and prioritization ability
Ability to work independently and autonomously, as well as part of a team
A Little More About Cirkul
Cirkul is a rapidly growing beverage technology company on a mission to make a healthier world by helping people enjoy drinking more water. The company has developed an innovative beverage delivery system that makes drinking more water delicious, fun, and personalized. The technology reduces the shipping weight of bottled beverages by 99% and uses 84% less plastic. Cirkul offers its customers over 50 unique flavors, all with no sugar, zero calories, zero carbs, no artificial colors or flavors, and a range of functional enhancements. Hundreds of thousands of consumers are using Cirkul to transition away from single-use plastics and sugar-filled beverages to healthier, better-for-you alternatives. The company is growing at a tremendous pace, is consistently profitable, and is backed by world class investors.

We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, protected veteran status, or disability status. JOB DESCRIPTION:
Overview:
Driven Brands Car Wash portfolio is the world’s largest car wash conglomerate. Driven Brands entered the car wash industry in 2020 with the acquisition of International Car Wash Group and operates over 900 locations in 14 countries across the US, Europe, and Australia. This role is on the team that supports over 360+ locations in the United States, and our mission is to be the most convenient car wash company in North America.
Driven Brands™, headquartered in Charlotte, NC, is the quintessential growth company, more than tripling its revenues, brands, employees, and profits over the past six years. Our culture of meritocracy inspires high performance and innovation among our employees. Driven Brands is the parent company of some of North America’s leading automotive aftermarket brands including Take 5 Car Wash®, Take 5 Oil Change®, Meineke Car Care Centers®, Maaco®, among others. Driven Brands has more than 4,500 locations across 15 countries, and services over 50 million vehicles annually. Driven Brands’ network generates more than $1.7 billion in annual revenue from more than $5.0 billion in system-wide sales. For more information, visit drivenbrands.com.
Responsibilities:
The Labor Analyst is responsible for building and enhancing the labor model supporting the US Car Wash portfolio which includes Take 5 Car Wash and other brands. The Labor Analyst will conduct studies and analyze data to determine how to maximize labor efficiency and capacity across the 400+ car wash sites, as well as those acquired or built.
Lead the deployment and implementation of labor management programs designed to optimize hourly payroll.
Interprets data to provide insights on operational impact, trends, and opportunities as well as identify outliers.
Actively partner with field operations leaders to ensure actual scheduling correlates to our ideal models and to continuously improve how we manage labor.
Assess the impact of labor allocation on business metrics and customer experience.
Integrates data from multiple sources to produce requested or required analysis.
Effectively collaborate with cross-functional business partners across the Driven Brands portfolios, especially Finance, HR and Marketing.
Play a critical role in the weekly, monthly and quarterly roll-up of labor management data and scorecards, partnering with the field operators on driving improvement.
Qualifications:
BA/BS degree or equivalent degree preferred
1+ years of experience required in relevant fields including Operations, Business Analytics, or Labor Relations
Intermediate Excel skills required
HRIS/WFM knowledge and experience preferred
Ability to quickly identify business problems/opportunities and take initiative to solve
Ability to communicate with all levels of management and company personnel
Ability to document, prepare and present data-driven presentations

This team provides ongoing training, maintenance, monitoring and promotion of data applications and reports to ensure data insights are widely known, accessible, and used to its fullest potential. This position helps develop and deploy world class data analytics at Intermountain Healthcare, one of the nation’s leading health systems. Using the Scaled Agile Framework®, Data Analysts will partner with business and clinical leaders, and data professionals across the organization, supporting our Mission to help people live the healthiest lives possible.

Partner with Analytic leadership to ensure customer priorities are understood and resourced. Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About Cirkul, Inc.
Cirkul is a venture backed, direct-to-consumer startup company that develops transformational hydration products that reimagine how flavored beverages are created, personalized, and enjoyed at home and on-the-go. You may have read about us going viral on TikTok (https://www.bizjournals.com/tampabay/inno/stories/news/2021/06/15/tampa-startup-hires-100-after-going-viral-on-tikto.html) or partnering with some great investors here (https://www.bevnet.com/news/2021/cirkul-closes-30m-series-b-led-by-af-ventures/).
Overview
Cirkul is looking for a Data Analyst to join our growing data team. You’ll be tackling challenges across Growth/Marketing, Finance, Retail, Manufacturing, Supply Chain, and Customer Support teams to quickly deliver insights, review and develop metrics, and develop business processes to scale analytics to support a hypergrowth business.
The ideal candidate must be able to roll up his/her sleeves to work independently and contribute to the output and results. He/she must have the ability to prioritize issues, deal with ambiguity and manage conflicting deadlines. The candidate should also be creative, data-driven, and aggressive in delivering results. This position will report directly to the VP Data & Analytics.
Responsibilities
Collect, analyze, and explain data to key stakeholders and executive leadership
Design and develop KPIs tracking business performance across departments
Monitor KPIs to identify potential opportunities to improve company performance
Be a data evangelist: collaborate with both technical and non-technical teammates to supplement decisions with quantitative evidence
Always be auditing: build and maintain processes to track data and troubleshoot errors
Build and automate tools to surface key data to stakeholders across a broad range of data literacy levels
Provide ad hoc analysis and forecasting as needed across a diverse set of teams
Evaluate reporting needs and work with key stakeholders to prioritize overall strategy of the data team in answering company goals
Qualifications
Data-driven, detail-oriented individual with excellent analysis and problem-solving abilities
Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field such as Accounting, Economics, Engineering, Finance, Math, or Statistics or equivalent coursework and work experience
4+ years of relevant industry experience – you have delivered insights in a technical environment and are comfortable doing so again from Day 1
2+ years of DTC, Ecommerce, and/or Retail experience
Fluency in data analysis and data-driven problem solving; a track record of using data to communicate results to key stakeholders
Excellent verbal and written communication skills: the ability to present complex data in a digestible format to stakeholders of all data literacy levels
Fluency with SQL and experience with building models in Excel
Comfortable creating dashboards in a BI framework such as PowerBI, Tableau, Looker, or comparable tools
Ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously: superb time management and prioritization ability
Ability to work independently and autonomously, as well as part of a team
A Little More About Cirkul
Cirkul is a rapidly growing beverage technology company on a mission to make a healthier world by helping people enjoy drinking more water. The company has developed an innovative beverage delivery system that makes drinking more water delicious, fun, and personalized. The technology reduces the shipping weight of bottled beverages by 99% and uses 84% less plastic. Cirkul offers its customers over 50 unique flavors, all with no sugar, zero calories, zero carbs, no artificial colors or flavors, and a range of functional enhancements. Hundreds of thousands of consumers are using Cirkul to transition away from single-use plastics and sugar-filled beverages to healthier, better-for-you alternatives. The company is growing at a tremendous pace, is consistently profitable, and is backed by world class investors.

We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, protected veteran status, or disability status. JOB DESCRIPTION:
Overview:
Driven Brands Car Wash portfolio is the world’s largest car wash conglomerate. Driven Brands entered the car wash industry in 2020 with the acquisition of International Car Wash Group and operates over 900 locations in 14 countries across the US, Europe, and Australia. This role is on the team that supports over 360+ locations in the United States, and our mission is to be the most convenient car wash company in North America.
Driven Brands™, headquartered in Charlotte, NC, is the quintessential growth company, more than tripling its revenues, brands, employees, and profits over the past six years. Our culture of meritocracy inspires high performance and innovation among our employees. Driven Brands is the parent company of some of North America’s leading automotive aftermarket brands including Take 5 Car Wash®, Take 5 Oil Change®, Meineke Car Care Centers®, Maaco®, among others. Driven Brands has more than 4,500 locations across 15 countries, and services over 50 million vehicles annually. Driven Brands’ network generates more than $1.7 billion in annual revenue from more than $5.0 billion in system-wide sales. For more information, visit drivenbrands.com.
Responsibilities:
The Labor Analyst is responsible for building and enhancing the labor model supporting the US Car Wash portfolio which includes Take 5 Car Wash and other brands. Actively partner with field operations leaders to ensure actual scheduling correlates to our ideal models and to continuously improve how we manage labor.
Assess the impact of labor allocation on business metrics and customer experience.
Integrates data from multiple sources to produce requested or required analysis.
Effectively collaborate with cross-functional business partners across the Driven Brands portfolios, especially Finance, HR and Marketing.
Play a critical role in the weekly, monthly and quarterly roll-up of labor management data and scorecards, partnering with the field operators on driving improvement.

Ability to quickly identify business problems/opportunities and take initiative to solve
Ability to communicate with all levels of management and company personnel

Title: Data Operations Analyst
Description:
ABOUT THIS POSITION
We are seeking a Data Operations Analyst to join Waystar. In this role, you will be responsible for maintaining the Revenue Capture Charge Integrity SaaS solution’s specialized and proprietary charge capture functionality, working collaboratively with internal resources to ensure the Charge Integrity SaaS Solution is providing excellent value to each client. This requires a comprehensive understanding of the Hospital and Health System revenue cycle. An ideal candidate for this position has an in depth understanding of medical coding for both inpatient and outpatient encounters and can logically identify missed revenue opportunities through either coding variances or missing charges. The ideal candidate can approach problem-solving challenges creatively and independently, has a strong attention to detail, and enjoys working in a fast-paced, collaborative and team-based environment.
WHAT YOU'LL DO
Supporting our data driven predictive analytics platform, we also have rule-based anomaly predictions. This position is responsible for identifying and developing rules-based algorithms for CPT Coding variances, DRG Anomaly, and missing charges on provider accounts. Additionally, performing updates and ongoing maintenance to data elements used in our predictive analytics tool based on industry coding updates.
Utilize SQL to update and maintain evidence-based charge integrity rules
Remain current on CPT, ICD-10 CM and PCS coding requirements
Recommend and assist in implementing solutions to complex issues
Effectively executes project work plans while retaining the ability to revise plans as dictated by evolving needs and/or requirements
WHAT YOU'LL NEED
Bachelor’s degree or RHIT
Knowledge of hospital and physician office charge capture best practices
Capable of analyzing large quantities of data, identifying patterns, and summarizing by priority
Demonstrates effective verbal and non-verbal communication skills, exercises sound judgment, and commitment to teamwork
Highly self-motivated, desire to succeed, and strong attention to detail
MS Office skills, especially MS Excel and MS PowerPoint, including the ability to capture and manipulate data at a high level in MS Excel spreadsheets
Understanding of SQL
ABOUT THE TEAM
The Client Operations, Clearinghouse + Payment Operations, and Business Transformation team at Waystar builds brand loyalty and ensures solution adoption and client success. From resolving concerns to maintaining positive relationships, the team works directly with clients to provide resources and tools to help achieve their healthcare revenue cycle goals. The team is split into two divisions: Health Systems + Hospitals (HS+H) and Ambulatory. The Health Systems + Hospitals division includes large health systems at a multi-level local or national scale. The Ambulatory division includes organizations such as provider groups and physician and specialty practices.
ABOUT WAYSTAR
Through a smart platform and better experience, Waystar helps providers simplify healthcare payments and yield powerful results throughout the complete revenue cycle.
Waystar’s healthcare payments platform combines innovative, cloud-based technology, robust data, and unparalleled client support to streamline workflows and improve financials so providers can focus on what matters most: their patients and communities. Waystar is trusted by 1M+ providers, 1K+ hospitals and health systems, and is connected to over 5K commercial and Medicaid/Medicare payers. We are deeply committed to living out our organizational values: honesty; kindness; passion; curiosity; fanatical focus; best work, always; making it happen; and joyful,
Waystar products have won multiple Best in KLAS® or Category Leader awards since 2010 and earned multiple #1 rankings from Black Book™ surveys since 2012. The Waystar platform supports more than 500,000 providers, 1,000 health systems and hospitals, and 5,000 payers and health plans. For more information, visit
waystar.com
or follow
@Waystar
on Twitter.
WAYSTAR PERKS
Competitive total rewards (base salary + bonus, if applicable)
Customizable benefits package (3 medical plans with Health Saving Account company match)
Generous paid time off starting at 3 weeks + 16 holidays, including your birthday and volunteer time
Paid parental leave (including maternity + paternity leave)
Education assistance opportunities and free LinkedIn Learning access
Free mental health and family planning programs, including adoption assistance and fertility support
401(K) program with company match

This professional will start off working with ASHLIN’s cloud-based visualization platform, CompassBI, powered by Sisense, on visualizing descriptive statistics and other key performance indicators and building ASHLIN’s library of dashboard templates. Additional projects will include supporting our team of project specialist in developing deliverables to our clients, based research and analysis methods, using statistical models on business data collected in field. Candidates should also be comfortable preparing routine as well as ad-hoc business reports and PowerPoint decks to present the information to senior management and clients.

Essential duties and responsibilities:

Develop visualizations using tools such as Tableau, PowerBI and/or Sisense
Use sophisticated data analysis methods to support project team in creating deliverable for client
Work with clients to devise methods to optimize data capturing schemes and overall program evaluation plan Perform statistical modeling (e.g. ANOVA) using statistical software applications such as R and SPSS
Work with Senior Database Architect(s) to develop analytical SQL queries and reports for tracking, trending, and interpreting business data
Perform ongoing data quality assessments, identify discrepancies/inconsistencies, and resolve them
Continually improve the end-to-end process of data collection, transformation, analysis, and reporting
Develop data management programs and forms for data entry and maintenance by end-users
Document data analysis and reporting architecture, designs, and write user guides
Other duties as defined by senior research team

Qualifications

To be successful in this position, the Data Analyst must have a minimum of 3 years’ experience in:
Data analysis, involved in both primary and secondary research using data to arrive at decision pertaining to marketing strategies
Ability to interpret complex data sets (quantitative and qualitative) into insights that lead to effective marketing strategies and frameworks

Strong data analysis modelling, specifically the successful candidate must be able to:
Conduct cross-tabular and ANOVA and other statistical analysis using R and/or SPSS
Interpret results of statistical analysis output and draw insights in order to make recommendations to senior management what steps to take
Present data, interpretation and resulting strategy in language that indicates a command of the material while at the same time making sense to lay persons who may not have a marketing and/or data analysis background

Develop data reports using the following tools and technologies:

MS-Excel (Pivot Tables, VBA, Power Pivot, H-Lookup, V-Lookup, Import/Export from/to external data sources)
Online Dashboards (e.g. Tableau, PowerBI, Sisense)
Expert level skills in the development of highly impactful PowerPoint slide decks
Development of scheduled and ad-hoc reports and analysis.

Working in a team environment with responsibility for delivery of timely and accurate business-critical reports and analysis:
Self-motivated and proactive, willing to drive a program of work to successful completion,
Strong oral/written communication, and presentation skills,
Ability to work with highly sensitive information and preserve the confidentiality of the information,
Detail oriented and capable of identifying and resolving data quality issues.

In addition, the following are highly desirable:

A minimum of 3 years’ experience with statistical analysis tools (e.g. R, SPSS)
A background in market research, or related disciplines
Working knowledge of relational databases (e.g. SQL)

Position requirements include:

At least a Bachelor’s Degree in Math, Probability & Statistics, or related data science field
Master’s degree in any of the above disciplines is highly desirable, or MBA
High proficiency with statistical analysis tools
Only open to candidates US Citizens and Permanent Residents currently authorized to work in the US

Title: Data Management Analyst (Remote)
Description:
**We are interested in every qualified applicant who is eligible to work remotely in the United States. However, we are not able to sponsor VISAs.

Are you a Data Management Analyst with experience in Data Management and/or Governance Applications? Are you looking for your next opportunity? If so, consider joining us on our mission of helping our communities achieve better health!

What Will be Your Purpose?
Data Management Analysts support Data Management Consultants, and work directly with data governance stakeholders, business leaders, subject matter experts, and other technology professionals to create and execute on data risk reduction or value improvement propositions. The scope of this work involves one or more of the following data management disciplines: reference data management, data protection, data stewardship, master data management, data platform management, data strategy or data enablement and capabilities. Applies data protection or business value requirements to design, document and recommend possible data management and governance solutions. Participates in the creation of business specifications and contributes to system specifications aligned with business requirement and needs. Provides input into data management and governance project plans. Prepares, maintains, and contributes to data management and governance deliverables and artifacts, including flow charts, conceptual models, policies, procedures, standards, desktop procedures, guides, glossaries, code sets, metrics, scorecards and reporting to assist with the ongoing operation and maintenance of data management and governance solutions. Assigned to complex projects, systems or initiatives related to ongoing organization data management and governance needs. Data Management Analysts lead efforts, oversee work results, provide meeting facilitation and training, and serve as data experts for other business, technical and analytic resources.

What You’ll be Doing?
Produces and maintains data management products and artifacts as part of operational- or project-based tasks and ensures necessary design considerations are made in alignment with documented requirements.
Contributes to the operational- or project-based analysis and documentation of data-related assets, sources, business, and technical requirements; identifies impacted areas/systems/technical and business processes; and evaluates solutions and best practices.
Participates in and provides consultation during the review of system requirements and functional design solutions for data assets, functionality and enhancements to existing data assets and functionalities.
Takes the initiative to seek out areas of improvement.
Contributes to final review of design specifications to ensure business stakeholder/end user/data consumer needs are met.
Researches and assists in developing approaches for identifying and Resolving system or data-related problems.
Participates in efforts to identify and evaluate alternative solutions.
Acts as a matrix leader - partnering with business and project leaders to ensure goals are achieved; and identifying opportunities and efficiencies and overcoming obstacles with projectized work.
Performs analysis for highly complex projects, systems, or initiatives.
Act as a mentor to other business, technical and analytics partners and analysts.
Works with technical staff to ensure system components and functional flow of / between components is compliant with documented requirements.
Ensures adherence to practices, standards, policies, and procedures.
Assists in executing tests or validations for various system components and data transformations / migrations.
Influences business/IT/analytics stakeholders by recommending decisions and solutions built on approved requirements, value propositions and business case roadmaps.

What You Must Have?
Required Work Experience: 6+ years related work experience in Data management, data governance, data quality improvement, data security, data protection, data analytics, data-focused business or systems analysis, application development, data architecture or comparable role.
Required Education: Related Bachelor’s degree or additional related equivalent work experience IT, Data or Analytics field.

Thorough knowledge of Information Technology systems supporting data management.
Demonstrated organizational, analytical, and interpersonal skills.
Demonstrated ability to meet customers' needs by understand business drivers, process and data needs and translate them into implementable data solutions that create value for the organization.
Strong understanding of integration points of assigned business/systems and processes.
Proven leadership abilities including effective knowledge sharing, conflict resolution, facilitation of open discussions, fairness and displaying appropriate levels of assertiveness.
Proficient in requirements gathering methodologies and the software development life cycle (SDLC).
Understanding of a variety of architecture standards and ability to apply them in their design work.
Proven communication skills, with the ability to convey technical information in a meaningful way (technical and business).
Strong problem solving and critical thinking skills to evaluate alternatives and present solutions that are consistent with business objectives and strategy.
Extensive knowledge and experience of systems, subsystems, development methodologies, systems architecture, tools, and processes that support the assigned business initiative or system.
Experience in applying continuous improvement, DMAIC, data/process analysis or other similar methodologies to business solutions.
Knowledge of systems development concepts and methods.
Experience with business requirements and business process analysis to ensure IT solutions meet the business needs.
Experience managing multiple priorities and ability to facilitate adoption of changing priorities.
Demonstrated negotiation skills and ability to build relationships.
Experience interacting with data systems (like Oracle, SQL Server, IBM DB2, or Hadoop/HBase).
Experience writing database queries in languages like SQL or SAS.

What is Preferred?
Health care or health insurance industry related experience.
Data management or data governance related experience.
Experience with business, technical, and data process engineering.
Experience using Agile methodologies (like SAFe).
Experience using Agile project management applications (like Broadcom Rally).
Experience with quality assurance tools (like HP ALM).
Experience with data management and governance applications (like Informatica).
Preferred Education: Technology, Data or Analytics Degree.

General Physical Demands:
Sedentary work: Exerting up to 10 pounds of force occasionally to move objects. Jobs are sedentary if traversing activities are required only occasionally.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Title: Data Analyst
Duration: TBA
Location: Washington, DC
Education: Masters in Public Health, Epidemiology or Statistics Required
Classification: Temporary full-time exempt
The Public Sector Solutions Group (PS2G) is a technology driven company that provides innovative solutions to state and local government partners which enable them to achieve their performance goals and better service constituents at the most critical point of need. Our team leverages a deep knowledge of government programs, IT management systems, application development and specialized technical expertise to help clients achieve their performance goals while ensuring audit compliance and reporting for federally funded agencies.
PS2G is seeking a full-time temporary Data Analyst. DC Health collects data for two databases, the National Violent Death Reporting System (NVDRS) and the State Unintentional Drug Overdose Reporting System (SUDORS).
The National Violent Death Reporting System (NVDRS) currently functions as a public health surveillance system generated by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). DC HEALTH also collects data as part of the CDC’s Firearm Injury Surveillance Through Emergency Rooms (FASTER) program. An analyst is needed to work with this data and respond to ad hoc tasks like data cleaning, reporting and general program activities.
Experience:
A minimum of 2 years of experience performing data management, analysis, and reporting duties in a public health setting.
Responsibilities:
1.) Respond to inbound calls in a timely and professional manner and following identified procedures to respond, document, log, and notify the appropriate persons.
2.) Ensure that reporting remains current;
3.) Timely and accurate submission of all reports with an error rate no greater than 5%.
4.) Perform descriptive analyses of public health data using statistical software (SAS preferred) and produce daily reports and other analytical reports as needed.
5.) Ensuring data quality and integrity, perform tasks such as electronic file transfers; listing and tabulation of data for preparation of statistical reports; and electronic file linkages.
6.) Develop analytic datasets (to include, for example, data extraction, data cleaning, matching/merging, and variable coding) and document processes in codebooks, protocols, and associated guidance documents.
7.) Design databases and tracking systems and monitor data collection activities for multiple surveillance programs.
8. ) Utilize business analytics tools, such as Tableau, to perform data analysis. Support design and recommend content, format, dissemination methods, etc. Maintain and automate reporting applications and visualizations.
9.) Monitor quality assurance and quality improvement of applicable surveillance and other data systems and processes.
10.) Develop strategies for improving data processing efficiency, as well as data completeness and quality.
11.) Other duties as assigned
Knowledge Skills and Abilities
Strong understanding of statistics: A data analyst must have a solid foundation in statistics, including knowledge of statistical concepts such as mean, median, standard deviation, regression analysis, and hypothesis testing.
Data analysis tools: Proficiency in tools such as SQL, Python, R, Excel, and Tableau is essential for a data analyst. Knowledge of machine learning and artificial intelligence is also becoming increasingly important.
Data visualization: The ability to create compelling and informative data visualizations is essential for a data analyst. This includes knowledge of tools such as Tableau, Power BI, and Excel.
Business acumen: A data analyst should have a good understanding of the business context in which they work. They should be able to translate data insights into actionable recommendations for business decisions.
Problem-solving skills: A data analyst should be able to identify problems and find solutions through data analysis. This requires the ability to break down complex problems into smaller, more manageable components.
Communication skills: A data analyst should be able to communicate complex data insights to stakeholders in a clear and concise manner. This requires the ability to present data visually and verbally, and to tailor communication to the audience.
Attention to detail: A data analyst should have a keen eye for detail and be able to identify errors or inconsistencies in data.
Continuous learning: A data analyst should be committed to continuous learning and development, keeping up-to-date with new tools, techniques, and technologies in the field.

Title: Data Management Analyst (Remote)
Description:
**We are interested in every qualified applicant who is eligible to work remotely in the United States. However, we are not able to sponsor VISAs.

Are you a Data Management Analyst with experience in Data Management and/or Governance Applications? Are you looking for your next opportunity? If so, consider joining us on our mission of helping our communities achieve better health!

What Will be Your Purpose?
Data Management Analysts support Data Management Consultants, and work directly with data governance stakeholders, business leaders, subject matter experts, and other technology professionals to create and execute on data risk reduction or value improvement propositions. The scope of this work involves one or more of the following data management disciplines: reference data management, data protection, data stewardship, master data management, data platform management, data strategy or data enablement and capabilities. Applies data protection or business value requirements to design, document and recommend possible data management and governance solutions. Participates in the creation of business specifications and contributes to system specifications aligned with business requirement and needs. Provides input into data management and governance project plans. Prepares, maintains, and contributes to data management and governance deliverables and artifacts, including flow charts, conceptual models, policies, procedures, standards, desktop procedures, guides, glossaries, code sets, metrics, scorecards and reporting to assist with the ongoing operation and maintenance of data management and governance solutions. Assigned to complex projects, systems or initiatives related to ongoing organization data management and governance needs. Data Management Analysts lead efforts, oversee work results, provide meeting facilitation and training, and serve as data experts for other business, technical and analytic resources.

What You’ll be Doing?
Produces and maintains data management products and artifacts as part of operational- or project-based tasks and ensures necessary design considerations are made in alignment with documented requirements.
Contributes to the operational- or project-based analysis and documentation of data-related assets, sources, business, and technical requirements; identifies impacted areas/systems/technical and business processes; and evaluates solutions and best practices.
Participates in and provides consultation during the review of system requirements and functional design solutions for data assets, functionality and enhancements to existing data assets and functionalities.
Takes the initiative to seek out areas of improvement.
Contributes to final review of design specifications to ensure business stakeholder/end user/data consumer needs are met.
Researches and assists in developing approaches for identifying and Resolving system or data-related problems.
Participates in efforts to identify and evaluate alternative solutions.
Acts as a matrix leader - partnering with business and project leaders to ensure goals are achieved; and identifying opportunities and efficiencies and overcoming obstacles with projectized work.
Performs analysis for highly complex projects, systems, or initiatives.
Act as a mentor to other business, technical and analytics partners and analysts.
Works with technical staff to ensure system components and functional flow of / between components is compliant with documented requirements.
Ensures adherence to practices, standards, policies, and procedures.
Assists in executing tests or validations for various system components and data transformations / migrations.
Influences business/IT/analytics stakeholders by recommending decisions and solutions built on approved requirements, value propositions and business case roadmaps.

What You Must Have?
Required Work Experience: 6+ years related work experience in Data management, data governance, data quality improvement, data security, data protection, data analytics, data-focused business or systems analysis, application development, data architecture or comparable role.
Required Education: Related Bachelor’s degree or additional related equivalent work experience IT, Data or Analytics field.

Thorough knowledge of Information Technology systems supporting data management.
Demonstrated organizational, analytical, and interpersonal skills.
Demonstrated ability to meet customers' needs by understand business drivers, process and data needs and translate them into implementable data solutions that create value for the organization.
Strong understanding of integration points of assigned business/systems and processes.
Proven leadership abilities including effective knowledge sharing, conflict resolution, facilitation of open discussions, fairness and displaying appropriate levels of assertiveness.
Proficient in requirements gathering methodologies and the software development life cycle (SDLC).
Understanding of a variety of architecture standards and ability to apply them in their design work.
Proven communication skills, with the ability to convey technical information in a meaningful way (technical and business).
Strong problem solving and critical thinking skills to evaluate alternatives and present solutions that are consistent with business objectives and strategy.
Extensive knowledge and experience of systems, subsystems, development methodologies, systems architecture, tools, and processes that support the assigned business initiative or system.
Experience in applying continuous improvement, DMAIC, data/process analysis or other similar methodologies to business solutions.
Knowledge of systems development concepts and methods.
Experience with business requirements and business process analysis to ensure IT solutions meet the business needs.
Experience managing multiple priorities and ability to facilitate adoption of changing priorities.
Demonstrated negotiation skills and ability to build relationships.
Experience interacting with data systems (like Oracle, SQL Server, IBM DB2, or Hadoop/HBase).
Experience writing database queries in languages like SQL or SAS.

What is Preferred?
Health care or health insurance industry related experience.
Data management or data governance related experience.
Experience with business, technical, and data process engineering.
Experience using Agile methodologies (like SAFe).
Experience using Agile project management applications (like Broadcom Rally).
Experience with quality assurance tools (like HP ALM).
Experience with data management and governance applications (like Informatica).
Preferred Education: Technology, Data or Analytics Degree.

General Physical Demands:
Sedentary work: Exerting up to 10 pounds of force occasionally to move objects. Jobs are sedentary if traversing activities are required only occasionally.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Title: Data Analyst
Duration: TBA
Location: Washington, DC
Education: Masters in Public Health, Epidemiology or Statistics Required
Classification: Temporary full-time exempt
The Public Sector Solutions Group (PS2G) is a technology driven company that provides innovative solutions to state and local government partners which enable them to achieve their performance goals and better service constituents at the most critical point of need. Our team leverages a deep knowledge of government programs, IT management systems, application development and specialized technical expertise to help clients achieve their performance goals while ensuring audit compliance and reporting for federally funded agencies.
PS2G is seeking a full-time temporary Data Analyst. DC Health collects data for two databases, the National Violent Death Reporting System (NVDRS) and the State Unintentional Drug Overdose Reporting System (SUDORS).
The National Violent Death Reporting System (NVDRS) currently functions as a public health surveillance system generated by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). DC HEALTH also collects data as part of the CDC’s Firearm Injury Surveillance Through Emergency Rooms (FASTER) program. An analyst is needed to work with this data and respond to ad hoc tasks like data cleaning, reporting and general program activities.
Experience:
A minimum of 2 years of experience performing data management, analysis, and reporting duties in a public health setting.
Responsibilities:
1.) Respond to inbound calls in a timely and professional manner and following identified procedures to respond, document, log, and notify the appropriate persons.
2.) Ensure that reporting remains current;
3.) Timely and accurate submission of all reports with an error rate no greater than 5%.
4.) Perform descriptive analyses of public health data using statistical software (SAS preferred) and produce daily reports and other analytical reports as needed.
5.) Ensuring data quality and integrity, perform tasks such as electronic file transfers; listing and tabulation of data for preparation of statistical reports; and electronic file linkages.
6.) Develop analytic datasets (to include, for example, data extraction, data cleaning, matching/merging, and variable coding) and document processes in codebooks, protocols, and associated guidance documents.
7.) Design databases and tracking systems and monitor data collection activities for multiple surveillance programs.
8. ) Utilize business analytics tools, such as Tableau, to perform data analysis. Support design and recommend content, format, dissemination methods, etc. Maintain and automate reporting applications and visualizations.
9.) Monitor quality assurance and quality improvement of applicable surveillance and other data systems and processes.
10.) Develop strategies for improving data processing efficiency, as well as data completeness and quality.
11.) Other duties as assigned
Knowledge Skills and Abilities
Strong understanding of statistics: A data analyst must have a solid foundation in statistics, including knowledge of statistical concepts such as mean, median, standard deviation, regression analysis, and hypothesis testing.
Data analysis tools: Proficiency in tools such as SQL, Python, R, Excel, and Tableau is essential for a data analyst. Knowledge of machine learning and artificial intelligence is also becoming increasingly important.
Data visualization: The ability to create compelling and informative data visualizations is essential for a data analyst. This includes knowledge of tools such as Tableau, Power BI, and Excel.
Business acumen: A data analyst should have a good understanding of the business context in which they work. They should be able to translate data insights into actionable recommendations for business decisions.
Problem-solving skills: A data analyst should be able to identify problems and find solutions through data analysis. This requires the ability to break down complex problems into smaller, more manageable components.
Communication skills: A data analyst should be able to communicate complex data insights to stakeholders in a clear and concise manner. This requires the ability to present data visually and verbally, and to tailor communication to the audience.
Attention to detail: A data analyst should have a keen eye for detail and be able to identify errors or inconsistencies in data.
Continuous learning: A data analyst should be committed to continuous learning and development, keeping up-to-date with new tools, techniques, and technologies in the field.
